'''Christian Mate Pulisic''' ({{langx|hr|Pulišić}};{{efn|Both the anglicized pronunciation ({{IPAc-en|IPA|p|ə|ˈ|l|ɪ|s|ɪ|k}} {{respell|pə|LISS|ik}}) and the original Croatian pronunciation ({{ipa|hr|pǔliʃitɕ|IPA}}, {{small|approximated as}} {{IPAc-en|ˈ|p|ʊ|l|ɪ|ʃ|ɪ|tʃ}} {{respell|PUUL|ish|itch}}) have been used by commentators, and Pulisic confirmed that either form is acceptable.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Trifunović |first=Boris |date=September 21, 2019 |title=Pulišić: Ponosan sam na svoje korijene i htio bih naučiti jezik |language=hr |publisher=24sata |url=https://m.24sata.hr/sport/pulisic-ponosan-sam-na-svoje-korijene-i-htio-bih-nauciti-jezik-649831 |access-date=October 27, 2019 |archive-date=October 27, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191027073147/https://m.24sata.hr/sport/pulisic-ponosan-sam-na-svoje-korijene-i-htio-bih-nauciti-jezik-649831 |url-status=live}}</ref>}} born September 18, 1998) is an American professional [[Association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]], [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] and [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{Italian football updater|Milan}} club [[AC Milan]] and the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States national team]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Christian Pulisic – USMNT – US Mens Soccer Official Site |url=http://www.ussoccer.com/players/2014/03/15/05/12/christian-pulisic#tab-5 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160130192112/http://www.ussoccer.com/players/2014/03/15/05/12/christian-pulisic#tab-5 |archive-date=January 30, 2016 |access-date=January 26, 2016 |website=US Soccer}}</ref> Regarded as one of the best <!-- DO NOT CHANGE WITHOUT CONSENSUS--> North American players of all time, he is nicknamed "[[Captain America]]"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kinsella |first1=Nizaar |title=Why is Christian Pulisic called 'Captain America'? USMNT star's nickname explained |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/why-is-christian-pulisic-called-captain-america-usmnt-stars-nickname-explained/15i2b4qqmton1kznplkm7uez4 |access-date=March 26, 2025 |work=Goal |date=July 19, 2021}}</ref> and known for his dribbling, directness, and playmaking.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-11-15 |title=Talking tactics: By empowering Christian Pulisic, stresssing spacing and movement, something meaningful is forming for Mauricio Pochettino and the USMNT {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/talking-tactics-by-empowering-christian-pulisic-and-setting-a-structure-something-meaningful-is-forming-for-mauricio-pochettino-s-usmnt/bltd226937141fa35fc |access-date=2025-04-30 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=":16">{{Cite web |date=2025-04-04 |title=USMNT star Christian Pulisic reveals his 'target' in No. 10 role - with AC Milan talisman filling playmaking post for club & country {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/usmnt-christian-pulisic-target-no-10-milan-playmaking-club-country/blt2297feebf91c9dac |access-date=2025-04-30 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref>

Born and raised in [[Hershey, Pennsylvania]], Pulisic began his professional career at [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia Dortmund]], where he progressed quickly through the [[Borussia Dortmund Youth Sector|team's youth academy]], featuring in only 15 youth games. After being promoted to the senior team in January 2016 at age 17, he became the then-youngest player to score multiple goals in Bundesliga history.<ref>{{cite news |last=Uersfeld |first=Stephan |date=January 5, 2016 |title=U.S. youngster Christian Pulisic trains with Borussia Dortmund first team |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/borussia-dortmund/story/2780485/us-christian-pulisic-trains-with-dortmund-first-team?src=com |website=ESPN |access-date=January 2, 2019 |archive-date=October 29, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221029174911/https://www.espn.com/soccer/borussia-dortmund/story/2780485/us-christian-pulisic-trains-with-dortmund-first-team?src=com |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=American teenager Pulisic becomes youngest to score 2 Bunde… |url=https://thescore.com/bund/news/1013679 |access-date=2026-06-05 |website=thescore.com |language=en}}</ref> His involvement began increasing dramatically in the following [[2016–17 Borussia Dortmund season|2]][[2016–17 DFB-Pokal|016–17]] season, where he was a mainstay in the Dortmund team that won the [[2016–17 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]].<ref>{{cite magazine |title=USA's Pulisic a fast-rising talent at Dortmund |url=https://www.si.com/planet-futbol/2016/01/21/christian-pulisic-usa-borussia-dortmund |magazine=Sports Illustrated |access-date=January 26, 2016 |first=Liviu |last=Bird |date=January 20, 2016 |archive-date=October 17, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191017001800/https://www.si.com/planet-futbol/2016/01/21/christian-pulisic-usa-borussia-dortmund |url-status=live}}</ref> His performances made him runner-up of the [[2018 Ballon d'Or#Kopa Trophy|2018]] [[Kopa Trophy]]; presented to the world's best player under the age of 21.<ref name=":13" />

In January 2019, Pulisic moved to [[Premier League]] club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in a transfer worth $73 million (£57.6 million), making him the [[List of most expensive association football transfers|most expensive North American player of all time]], and began playing for the club in the [[2019–20 Chelsea F.C. season|2019–20 season]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2019/01/02/chelsea-sign-borussia-dortmund-winger-christian-pulisic-576m/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220111/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2019/01/02/chelsea-sign-borussia-dortmund-winger-christian-pulisic-576m/ |archive-date=January 11, 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Chelsea strike early in transfer window to sign Borussia Dortmund winger Christian Pulisic for £57.6m |first=Matt |last=Law |newspaper=The Telegraph |date=January 2, 2019}}{{cbignore}}</ref> During the [[2020–21 Chelsea F.C. season|following season]], he won the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League]], where he became the first American to play in a [[UEFA Champions League final|Champions League final]]. In the [[2021–22 Chelsea F.C. season|2021–22]] season, he won the [[2021 UEFA Super Cup]] and [[2021 FIFA Club World Cup]].<ref name=":8" /> Pulisic moved to [[Serie A]] club [[AC Milan]] in June 2023, beginning in the [[2023–24 AC Milan season|2023–24]] season and won the [[2024–25 Supercoppa Italiana]].<ref name=":10">{{cite web |date=May 2018 |title=Masters of Modern Soccer: Christian Pulisic and the Craft of the Attacking Midfielder |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2018/05/01/christian-pulisic-dortmund-usmnt-masters-modern-soccer |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190708052814/https://www.si.com/soccer/2018/05/01/christian-pulisic-dortmund-usmnt-masters-modern-soccer |archive-date=July 8, 2019 |access-date=October 28, 2019 |website=SI}}</ref> He is both the all-time top American goalscorer and assist provider in the European [[Big Five (association football)|top five leagues]] and the [[UEFA Champions League]].<ref name=":23" /><ref name=":24">{{Cite web |title=Most Champions League Goals By An American |url=https://www.statmuse.com/fc/ask/most-champions-league-goals-by-an-american |access-date=2026-05-29 |website=StatMuse |language=en}}</ref>

Pulisic played for the United States at [[United States boys' national under-15 soccer team|under-15]] and [[United States men's national under-17 soccer team|under-17]] levels, before making his senior national team debut in March 2016 at age 17. He became the youngest player ever to captain the United States national team at age 20.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/sports/soccer/ct-spt-us-italy-christian-pulisic-20181120-story.html |title=Christian Pulisic, 20, becomes youngest in modern era to captain U.S. men's national team in 1–0 loss to Italy |website=Chicago Tribune |date=November 20, 2018 |access-date=January 9, 2020 |archive-date=December 1, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221201073451/https://www.chicagotribune.com/sports/soccer/ct-spt-us-italy-christian-pulisic-20181120-story.html |url-status=live}}</ref> At the [[CONCACAF Gold Cup]], Pulisic was named the best young player of the [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2019]] tournament. He won the [[CONCACAF Nations League]] in [[2021 CONCACAF Nations League Finals|2021]], [[2023 CONCACAF Nations League Finals|2023]] and [[2024 CONCACAF Nations League Finals|2024]], winning the best player award of the 2023 tournament. Individually, he is tied with [[Landon Donovan]] for the record of four [[U.S. Soccer Player of the Year|U.S. Player of the Year]] awards and is his country's fifth-highest [[USMNT#Individual records|all-time leading goalscorer]]. He has been widely viewed as the "face" of [[Soccer in the United States|American soccer]].<ref>{{cite web |date=June 16, 2021 |title=Christian Pulisic on being the face of American soccer: 'I can't believe that I've got to this point so soon' |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/christian-pulisic-on-being-the-face-of-american-soccer-i-cant-believe-that-ive-got-to-this-point-so-soon/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230416021550/https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/christian-pulisic-on-being-the-face-of-american-soccer-i-cant-believe-that-ive-got-to-this-point-so-soon/ |archive-date=April 16, 2023 |access-date=April 16, 2023 |website=CBS Sports}}</ref>

== Early life ==
Pulisic was born in [[Hershey, Pennsylvania]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/players/p/christian-pulisic |title=Men's national team: Christian Pulisic |publisher=United States Soccer Federation |access-date=July 30, 2018 |archive-date=August 12, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812220153/https://www.ussoccer.com/players/p/christian-pulisic |url-status=live}}</ref> where he spent the majority of his childhood. His parents, Kelley and [[Mark Pulisic]], both played collegiate soccer at [[George Mason University]] and his father also played professional [[indoor soccer]] for the [[Harrisburg Heat (NPSL/MISL)|Harrisburg Heat]] in the 1990s and later became a coach at the youth, collegiate, and professional levels.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bbiY0Sk1G0g |title=Das American: Christian Pulisic's Spectacular Rise |last=VICE Sports |date=November 9, 2016 |via=YouTube |access-date=November 13, 2016 |archive-date=November 13, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113203741/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bbiY0Sk1G0g&gl=US&hl=en |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Year-by-Year Results |url=https://godutchmen.com/sports/2020/5/19/msoc-year-by-year-results.aspx?id=300 |access-date=2025-01-25 |website=Lebanon Valley College Athletics |language=en}}</ref> Growing up, his soccer idol was [[Luís Figo]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2020/04/21/christian-pulisic-reveals-his-footballing-idol-growing-up-and-wh |title=Pulisic reveals his footballing idol growing up and who he would love to play alongside now |website=Chelsea F.C. |date=April 21, 2020|access-date=February 6, 2021|archive-date=April 11, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411101823/https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2020/04/21/christian-pulisic-reveals-his-footballing-idol-growing-up-and-wh|url-status=live}}</ref>

While his mother was on a teacher exchange in England through the [[Fulbright Program]], Pulisic lived for a year in [[Tackley]], [[Oxfordshire]].<ref name="theguardian.com" /> At age seven, he began playing for the youth team of [[Brackley Town F.C.|Brackley Town]].<ref name="theguardian.com" /> When his father was general manager of indoor club [[Detroit Ignition]] in the mid-2000s, Pulisic lived in Michigan and played for Michigan Rush. While in Michigan, he attended [[Plymouth-Canton Community Schools|Workman Elementary School]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/how-did-christian-pulisic-make-it-into-the-european-big-leagues-dortmund-2765-1243 |title=How did Borussia Dortmund star Christian Pulisic make it into the European big leagues? |website=bundesliga.com |language=en |first=Andy |last=Smith |date=2018 |access-date=January 14, 2021 |archive-date=December 20, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201220152733/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/how-did-christian-pulisic-make-it-into-the-european-big-leagues-dortmund-2765-1243 |url-status=live}}</ref>

== Club career ==
After the family returned to the Hershey area, Pulisic grew up playing for local [[U.S. Soccer Development Academy]] club PA Classics and occasionally training with local professional club Harrisburg City Islanders, now known as [[Harrisburg City Islanders|Penn FC]], during his teen years. In the summer of 2010, he went on a five-day trial at [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]'s [[Cobham Training Centre|Cobham base]].<ref>{{cite web |date=August 12, 2020 |title=Pulisic, Mount and Carlton – the story behind this Chelsea picture |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/1989304/2020/08/12/pulisic-mount-carlton-chelsea-trials-picture-academy/ |website=The Athletic |access-date=May 5, 2021 |archive-date=April 30, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210430214556/https://theathletic.com/1989304/2020/08/12/pulisic-mount-carlton-chelsea-trials-picture-academy/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Borussia Dortmund ===
Pulisic moved to Germany before his 16th birthday. He became eligible because, as his grandfather was [[Croats|Croatian]], he could get a European passport and play starting at age 16 rather than 18. He initially had issues getting the passport, but it eventually panned out.<ref name=":5">{{Cite web |date=November 16, 2022 |title=How Christian Pulisic became American soccer's reticent and resilient trailblazer |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/how-christian-pulisic-became-american-soccers-reticent-and-resilient-trailblazer-181052557.html |access-date=November 16, 2022 |website=sports.yahoo.com |language=en-US |archive-date=November 16, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221116075055/https://sports.yahoo.com/how-christian-pulisic-became-american-soccers-reticent-and-resilient-trailblazer-181052557.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

In February 2015, [[Borussia Dortmund]] signed 16-year-old Pulisic and assigned him first to their U17 squad, winning the [[Under 17 Bundesliga]] in 2014–15. He was immediately promoted in summer 2015 to the U19 squad and won the [[Under 19 Bundesliga]] for the 2015–16 season.<ref name="id.soccerway.com">{{Cite web |title=Klasemen - U19 Bundesliga - Jerman - Results, fixtures, tables and news - Soccerway |url=https://id.soccerway.com/national/germany/u-19-bundesliga/20152016/west/r32283/tables/ |access-date=2024-02-21 |website=id.soccerway.com}}</ref> After scoring 10 goals and assisting 8 in just 15 games with the [[Borussia Dortmund Youth Sector|Dortmund youth teams]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Who is US international Christian Pulisic, and how did he make the Borussia Dortmund first team at 17 years old? |url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2016/01/31/who-us-international-christian-pulisic-and-how-did-he-make-borussia-dortmund-first |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127071705/https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2016/01/31/who-us-international-christian-pulisic-and-how-did-he-make-borussia-dortmund-first |archive-date=November 27, 2020 |access-date=June 25, 2023 |work=MLSsoccer.com}}</ref> Pulisic was called to join the first team over winter break.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Der nächste Schritt für Passlack und Pulisic |url=https://www.kicker.de/der-naechste-schritt-fuer-passlack-und-pulisic-642270/artikel |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181029155545/http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/startseite/642270/artikel_der-naechste-schritt-fuer-passlack-und-pulisic.html |archive-date=October 29, 2018 |access-date=January 26, 2016 |newspaper=Kicker}}</ref>

==== 2015–16: Breakthrough season ====
In January 2016, while with the first team in the winter break, Pulisic played the second half of two friendly matches, scoring one goal and assisting another.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Christian Pulisic scores in Dortmund win |url=http://sbisoccer.com/2016/01/christian-pulisic-scores-in-dortmund-win |website=Soccer By Ives |date=January 15, 2016 |access-date=January 26, 2016 |language=en-US |archive-date=October 21, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021035711/https://sbisoccer.com/2016/01/christian-pulisic-scores-in-dortmund-win |url-status=live}}</ref> On January 24, a day after making his debut on the first team bench, Pulisic played 90 minutes in a friendly against [[1. FC Union Berlin|Union Berlin]], scoring a goal and assisting another.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Christian Pulisic scores second friendly goal of month for Dortmund |url=http://sbisoccer.com/2016/01/christian-pulisic-scores-second-goal-of-month-for-dortmund |website=Soccer By Ives |date=January 24, 2016 |access-date=January 26, 2016 |language=en-US |archive-date=October 26, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026063624/https://sbisoccer.com/2016/01/christian-pulisic-scores-second-goal-of-month-for-dortmund |url-status=live}}</ref> He made his Bundesliga debut in a 2–0 win against [[FC Ingolstadt 04|Ingolstadt]] on January 30, 2016, coming on as a second-half substitute for [[Adrián Ramos]].<ref>{{cite news |title=American 17-year-old Christian Pulisic makes Bundesliga debut for Dortmund |url=http://www.espnfc.us/borussia-dortmund/story/2797405/american-christian-pulisic-makes-bundesliga-debut-at-age-17 |access-date=January 30, 2016 |publisher=ESPN FC |date=January 30, 2016 |archive-date=June 9, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609002251/http://www.espnfc.us/borussia-dortmund/story/2797405/american-christian-pulisic-makes-bundesliga-debut-at-age-17 |url-status=live}}</ref> On February 18, Pulisic made his [[UEFA Europa League]] debut as a second-half substitute in a 2–0 victory against [[FC Porto|Porto]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2017168--b-dortmund-vs-porto/ |title=Dortmund deal Porto heavy blow |work=[[UEFA]] |access-date=April 17, 2016 |archive-date=October 31, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191031131828/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2016/matches/round=2000659/match=2017168/index.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

Pulisic made his first [[Bundesliga]] start on February 21, against [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]], before eventually being substituted for [[Marco Reus]]. He made his second Bundesliga start on April 10, against [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] in the ''[[Revierderby]]'', playing 73 minutes before being replaced by [[İlkay Gündoğan]]. In response to Pulisic's performance against Schalke, team manager [[Thomas Tuchel]] said, "He's a teenager in his first year of professional football. His first two games in the starting eleven were in Leverkusen and here today in Schalke – not the easiest of tasks. It shows our huge appreciation that we see him as a full time player on our team. He was a valuable substitute against [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] and [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]]. He has looked really good recently which has been proved today. It is completely normal that he could not have played with this pace and this intensity for over 90 minutes."<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://screamer.deadspin.com/christian-pulisic-is-more-than-just-the-next-hyped-savi-1770345385 |title=Christian Pulisic, The Latest "Savior Of American Soccer," Is More Than Just Hype |last=Redford |first=Patrick |website=Screamer |date=April 12, 2016 |language=en-US |access-date=April 12, 2016 |archive-date=September 19, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919194239/http://screamer.deadspin.com/christian-pulisic-is-more-than-just-the-next-hyped-savi-1770345385 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Pulisic scored his first Bundesliga goal for Borussia Dortmund on April 17, opening the scoring in a 3–0 home win against [[Hamburger SV|Hamburg]]. It made him the youngest non-German and fourth-youngest player to score a goal in the Bundesliga, at 17 years and 212 days old.<ref name="youngest">{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/borussia-dortmund/story/2852892/christian-pulisic-youngest-non-german-to-score-in-bundesliga |title=Christian Pulisic becomes youngest non-German to score in Bundesliga |work=ESPNFC.com |date=April 17, 2016 |access-date=April 17, 2016 |archive-date=July 31, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190731163847/http://www.espnfc.com/borussia-dortmund/story/2852892/christian-pulisic-youngest-non-german-to-score-in-bundesliga |url-status=live}}</ref> With his goal against [[VfB Stuttgart]] on April 23, Pulisic broke another Bundesliga scoring record by becoming the youngest player to score two goals in the top-flight league. The game also marked his first [[Penalty card#Yellow card|yellow card]] in the Bundesliga, as a result of a challenge on [[Emiliano Insúa]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.foxsports.com/soccer/story/christian-pulisic-scores-again-to-become-youngest-player-ever-with-two-bundesliga-goals-042316 |title=Christian Pulisic scores again to become youngest player ever with 2 Bundesliga goals |work=FoxSports.com |access-date=April 23, 2016 |archive-date=April 4, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404164835/https://www.foxsports.com/soccer/story/christian-pulisic-scores-again-to-become-youngest-player-ever-with-two-bundesliga-goals-042316 |url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2016–19: DFB-Pokal win and departure ====
[[File:Christian Pulisic 2017 (cropped).jpg|alt=|thumb|Pulisic during a training session with [[Borussia Dortmund]]]]
In the [[2016 International Champions Cup]] friendly pre-season tournament, Pulisic scored in stoppage time against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] to send the clubs into [[Penalty shootout|penalties]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.us/match?gameId=446686 |title=Dortmund vs. Manchester City Recap |work=ESPNFC.com |access-date=July 28, 2016 |archive-date=October 8, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171008030140/http://www.espnfc.us/match?gameId=446686 |url-status=live}}</ref> During his first competitive appearance in his second year with the club, Pulisic became Dortmund's youngest player ever to play in the [[UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.foxsports.com/soccer/story/christian-pulisic-looked-great-in-his-first-ever-champions-league-match-091416 |title=Christian Pulisic looked great in his first ever Champions League match |work=FoxSports.com |access-date=September 17, 2016 |archive-date=February 4, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200204211247/https://www.foxsports.com/soccer/story/christian-pulisic-looked-great-in-his-first-ever-champions-league-match-091416 |url-status=live}}</ref> The following weekend he scored his first goal of the season and provided two assists in a 6–0 victory against [[SV Darmstadt 98|Darmstadt 98]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.foxsports.com/soccer/story/watch-christian-pulisic-score-for-borussia-dortmund-as-the-americans-hot-streak-continues-091716 |title=Watch Christian Pulisic score for Borussia Dortmund as the American's hot streak continues |work=FoxSports.com |access-date=September 17, 2016 |archive-date=August 9, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190809135248/https://www.foxsports.com/soccer/story/watch-christian-pulisic-score-for-borussia-dortmund-as-the-americans-hot-streak-continues-091716 |url-status=live}}</ref> one day before his 18th birthday.

In a September [[2016–17 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] [[2016–17 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group F|group stage]] game against [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]], with Dortmund trailing 2–1, Pulisic came on as a second-half substitute and helped set up [[André Schürrle]]'s late goal, allowing Dortmund to earn a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.us/borussia-dortmund/story/2960753/borussia-dortmund-christian-pulisic-describes-assist-on-andre-schurrle-goal-an-amazing-moment |title=Christian Pulisic describes Andre Schurrle leveler as 'amazing moment' |date=September 27, 2016|access-date=September 29, 2016|archive-date=July 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180724032441/http://www.espnfc.us/borussia-dortmund/story/2960753/borussia-dortmund-christian-pulisic-describes-assist-on-andre-schurrle-goal-an-amazing-moment|url-status=live}}</ref> In a substitute appearance on October 22, Pulisic assisted one goal and scored the equalizer against Ingolstadt 04, who were last place at the beginning of the day, to salvage a draw, coming back from 3–1 down.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/borussia-dortmund/story/2978874/christian-pulisic-dortmund-showed-good-heart-to-fight-back-for-draw |title=Christian Pulisic: Dortmund showed 'good heart' to fight back for draw |work=ESPN FC |date=October 22, 2016 |access-date=October 23, 2016 |archive-date=August 2, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190802161644/http://www.espnfc.com/borussia-dortmund/story/2978874/christian-pulisic-dortmund-showed-good-heart-to-fight-back-for-draw |url-status=live}}</ref>

On January 23, 2017, Pulisic signed a new deal with Dortmund which would keep him at the club until 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bvb.de/eng/News/Overview/Borussia-Dortmund-also-tie-Christian-Pulisic-to-the-club-for-the-long-term |title=Borussia Dortmund also tie Christian Pulisic to the club for the long-term |date=January 23, 2017 |access-date=January 23, 2017 |publisher=Borussia Dortmund |archive-date=November 11, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111231655/https://www.bvb.de/eng/News/Overview/Borussia-Dortmund-also-tie-Christian-Pulisic-to-the-club-for-the-long-term |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.espnfc.com/soccer-transfers/story/3044743/christian-pulisic-extends-borussia-dortmund-deal-until-2020 |title=Christian Pulisic extends Borussia Dortmund deal until 2020 |date=January 23, 2017 |access-date=January 23, 2017 |publisher=ESPN FC |archive-date=August 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190803215927/http://www.espnfc.com/soccer-transfers/story/3044743/christian-pulisic-extends-borussia-dortmund-deal-until-2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> On March 8, 2017, Pulisic scored his first UEFA Champions League goal in a 4–0 victory over [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in the round of 16, making him Dortmund's youngest ever scorer in the competition at the age of 18 years, 5 months, and 18 days.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.espnfc.com/borussia-dortmund/story/3078280/christian-pulisic-becomes-borussia-dortmunds-youngest-champions-league-goalscorer |title=Christian Pulisic becomes Dortmund's youngest UCL goalscorer |date=March 8, 2017 |work=ESPN |access-date=March 9, 2017 |archive-date=August 1, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190801171040/http://www.espnfc.com/borussia-dortmund/story/3078280/christian-pulisic-becomes-borussia-dortmunds-youngest-champions-league-goalscorer |url-status=live}}</ref> He was a victim of the [[Borussia Dortmund team bus bombing]] in April 2017, and was among his teammates who testified in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2018-04-25 |title=Pulisic testifies: 'I had problems' after attack |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37552274/christian-pulisic-borussia-dortmund-teammates-testify-bus-attack-trial |access-date=2025-08-23 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref>

Pulisic  assisted one of [[Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang]]'s goals in the win, advancing Dortmund to the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/soccer-insider/wp/2017/03/08/christian-pulisic-scores-in-uefa-champions-league-details-video/ |title=Christian Pulisic scores in UEFA Champions League: details, video |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |date=March 8, 2017 |access-date=March 9, 2017 |archive-date=October 23, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201023173019/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/soccer-insider/wp/2017/03/08/christian-pulisic-scores-in-uefa-champions-league-details-video/ |url-status=live}}</ref> On August 5, 2017, Pulisic scored the first goal in the [[2017 DFL-Supercup|DFL-Supercup]] against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/miss-dortmunds-bartra-hands-bayern-german-super-cup-205017688--sow.html |title=Miss by Dortmund's Bartra hands Bayern German Super Cup |date=August 5, 2017 |access-date=August 5, 2017 |archive-date=July 24, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180724032334/https://sports.yahoo.com/miss-dortmunds-bartra-hands-bayern-german-super-cup-205017688--sow.html |url-status=dead}}</ref>

Pulisic was on the final shortlist of the 2017 [[Golden Boy (award)|Golden Boy]] award, finishing 6th.<ref name=":26">{{Cite web |last=Egerton |first=Nathan |date=2022-12-14 |title=Revisiting the Golden Boy top 10 from 2017: Mbappe, Jesus, Mor... |url=https://www.planetfootball.com/quick-reads/2017-golden-boy-top-10-where-now-mbappe-mor-rashford-dembele |access-date=2025-08-23 |website=Planet Football |language=en}}</ref> In the following year, he was nominated final shortlist of the inaugural [[Kopa Trophy]], finishing runner-up to [[Kylian Mbappé]] during the [[2018 Ballon d'Or|2018 ceremony]].<ref name=":18">{{Cite web |last=Marsden |first=Rory |title=Kylian Mbappe and Christian Pulisic Head Revised 2018 Golden Boy Shortlist |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2793915-kylian-mbappe-and-christian-pulisic-head-revised-2018-golden-boy-shortlist |access-date=2024-09-26 |website=Bleacher Report |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":13" />

=== Chelsea ===
On January 2, 2019, Pulisic signed with [[Premier League]] club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] for an estimated £58&nbsp;million transfer fee. The deal also saw him stay at Dortmund on [[Loan (sports)|loan]] for the remainder of the [[2018–19 Borussia Dortmund season|2018–19 season]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Christian Pulisic: Chelsea sign Borussia Dortmund attacker for £58m |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46734487 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=January 2, 2019 |access-date=January 2, 2019 |archive-date=January 2, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102100243/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46734487 |url-status=live}}</ref> This transfer made Pulisic the [[List of most expensive American soccer transfers|most expensive American player]] and Borussia Dortmund's second most expensive sale of all time, behind [[Ousmane Dembélé]].<ref>{{cite news |last=O'Hanlon |first=Ryan |date=January 2, 2019 |title=Christian Pulisic Is Headed to Chelsea. Is American Soccer Ready? |url=https://slate.com/culture/2019/01/christian-pulisic-usmnt-chelsea-soccer-winning.html |work=[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]] |access-date=January 2, 2019 |archive-date=January 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190103064230/https://slate.com/culture/2019/01/christian-pulisic-usmnt-chelsea-soccer-winning.html |url-status=live}}</ref> Upon his arrival in the summer, he spoke of his desire to replicate the form shown by [[Eden Hazard]] and described the forward as a soccer idol.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://chasingacup.com/pulisic-and-hazard-beyond-comparison/ |title=Comparing Christian Pulisic and Eden Hazard |publisher=Chasingacup.com |access-date=September 14, 2020 |archive-date=October 3, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201003004652/https://chasingacup.com/pulisic-and-hazard-beyond-comparison/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48358517 |title=Christian Pulisic: New Chelsea signing wants to make same impact as Eden Hazard |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=May 22, 2019 |archive-date=May 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190522001157/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48358517 |url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2019–20: Debut season and Premier League breakthrough ====
[[File:Chelsea 1 Leicester 1 (48574907327).jpg|thumb|230x230px|Pulisic (pictured with [[Jamie Vardy]]) during a Premier League game against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] in August 2019]]
On August 11, 2019, Pulisic made his Premier League debut for Chelsea in a 4–0 defeat to [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/usmnt-star-pulisic-makes-chelsea-debut-as-substitute-against/47z49ki9pbx61d40mzbafl4rn |title=USMNT star Pulisic makes Chelsea debut as substitute against Manchester United |access-date=August 11, 2019 |archive-date=August 12, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812124047/https://www.goal.com/en/news/usmnt-star-pulisic-makes-chelsea-debut-as-substitute-against/47z49ki9pbx61d40mzbafl4rn |url-status=live}}</ref> Pulisic scored his first goals for Chelsea on October 26, 2019, completing a [[Hat-trick#Perfect hat-trick|"perfect" hat-trick]] in a 4–2 away win against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]]. The hat-trick was the first of his career, and he became the second American to achieve the feat in the Premier League after [[Clint Dempsey]] for [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] in 2012, as well as the youngest hat-trick scorer in Chelsea's history at the age of 21 years and 38 days.<ref name=":27">{{cite news |last=White |first=Marcus |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/bayarea/soccer/watch-usmnts-christian-pulisic-score-hat-trick-first-chelsea-goals |title=Watch USMNT's Christian Pulisic score hat trick, first Chelsea goals |website=[[NBC Sports]] |date=October 26, 2019 |access-date=October 26, 2019 |archive-date=October 22, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201022160915/https://www.nbcsports.com/bayarea/soccer/watch-usmnts-christian-pulisic-score-hat-trick-first-chelsea-goals |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Mendola |first=Nicholas |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/pulisic-bags-hat-trick-chelsea-182043623.html |title=Pulisic bags hat trick as Chelsea doubles up Burnley |website=[[Yahoo Sports]] |date=October 26, 2019 |access-date=October 26, 2019 |archive-date=October 19, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201019151726/https://sports.yahoo.com/pulisic-bags-hat-trick-chelsea-182043623.html |url-status=dead}}</ref> He also became the first Chelsea player to score a perfect hat trick since [[Didier Drogba]] in 2010.<ref>{{cite news |last=O'Brien |first=Sean |url=https://talksport.com/football/621277/christian-pulisic-chelsea-perfect-hat-trick-didier-drogba-incredible-stats/ |title=Facts: Christian Pulisic ends Chelsea wait for perfect hat-trick dating back to Didier Drogba era: The incredible stats behind American's treble |website=[[Talksport]] |date=October 27, 2019 |access-date=May 16, 2020 |archive-date=August 25, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200825174955/https://talksport.com/football/621277/christian-pulisic-chelsea-perfect-hat-trick-didier-drogba-incredible-stats/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Pulisic scored in his next two league outings, a 2–1 away victory against [[Watford FC|Watford]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Wilkinson |first=Jack |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/watford-vs-chelsea/408089 |title=Watford 1 – 2 Chelsea |website=Sky Sports |date=November 2, 2019 |access-date=November 10, 2019 |archive-date=November 9, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191109164444/https://www.skysports.com/football/watford-vs-chelsea/408089 |url-status=live}}</ref> and a 2–0 home win over [[Crystal Palace FC|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50271772 |title=Chelsea 2–0 Crystal Palace |website=BBC Sport |date=November 10, 2019 |access-date=November 9, 2019 |archive-date=October 24, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201024162314/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50271772 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On October 23, 2019, during a Champions League match against [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], Pulisic played as a substitute and assisted [[Michy Batshuayi]]'s late goal 1–0 win. The Belgium striker thumped home fellow substitute Pulisic's low cross with just four minutes remaining at [[Johan Cruyff Arena]] to earn the Blues back to back away wins in the competition.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/en/amp/news/ajax-0-1-chelsea-batshuayi-late-show-earns-huge-win-for/1wjol1epu0erj14b72jno4kqoq |title=Ajax 0–1 Chelsea: Batshuayi late show earns huge win for Blues |website=goal.com |date=October 10, 2019 |access-date=September 9, 2020 |archive-date=October 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024191225/https://www.goal.com/en/amp/news/ajax-0-1-chelsea-batshuayi-late-show-earns-huge-win-for/1wjol1epu0erj14b72jno4kqoq |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] goal for Chelsea in a 2–2 draw away to [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] on November 27.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50519896 |title=Valencia 2–2 Chelsea |website=BBC Sport |date=November 27, 2019 |access-date=November 28, 2019 |archive-date=October 20, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020094625/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50519896 |url-status=live}}</ref>

When the [[Premier League]] fixtures resumed after the lockdown due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]], Pulisic had recovered from injury and came off the bench to score the equalizer in Chelsea's 2–1 win against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] on June 21, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rose |first=Gary |date=June 21, 2020 |title=Aston Villa 1–2 Chelsea |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51779560 |access-date=June 25, 2020 |website=BBC Sport |archive-date=June 23, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200623090133/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51779560 |url-status=live}}</ref> In the following match, Pulisic scored the first goal in Chelsea's 2–1 victory over [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], a result that eliminated the second-placed City from title contention and confirmed Liverpool as Premier League champions.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Bevan |first=Chris |date=June 25, 2020 |title=Chelsea 2–1 Man CIty |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51884262 |access-date=June 25, 2020 |website=BBC Sport |archive-date=June 26, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626034146/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51884262 |url-status=live}}</ref> On July 22, Pulisic scored a goal in a 3–5 defeat to Liverpool.<ref>{{Cite web |last=McNulty |first=Phil |date=July 22, 2020 |title=Liverpool 5–3 Chelsea |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/53412782 |access-date=July 22, 2020 |website=BBC Sport |archive-date=July 22, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200722212438/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/53412782 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On August 1, he scored the opening goal in the [[2020 FA Cup Final]] against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] after five minutes, becoming the first American player to score in the final of the competition, but was substituted early in the second half after sustaining a [[Pulled hamstring|hamstring injury]]. Arsenal eventually came from behind to win the match 2–1.<ref name="bbc-2020FACupFinal">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53546100 |title=Arsenal 2–1 Chelsea |website=BBC Sport |first=Phil |last=McNulty |date=August 1, 2020 |access-date=August 2, 2020 |archive-date=August 1, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801202716/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53546100 |url-status=live}}</ref>

In August 2020, Pulisic was named to the eight-player shortlist for the inaugural [[Premier League Young Player of the Season]] award,<ref name ="2020 young player">{{Cite web |title=Vote for 2019/20 TAG Heuer Young Player of the Season |url=http://www.premierleague.com/news/1744535|access-date=August 7, 2020 |website=www.premierleague.com |language=en|archive-date=August 7, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200807150447/https://www.premierleague.com/news/1744535|url-status=live}}</ref> which was eventually awarded to Liverpool's [[Trent Alexander-Arnold]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/liverpool-engliverpool/story/4159360/liverpools-alexander-arnold-beats-rashford-pulisic-to-win-premier-league-young-player-of-the-season |title=Liverpool's Alexander-Arnold beats Rashford, Pulisic to win Premier League Young Player of the Season |date=August 14, 2020 |website=ESPN.com|access-date=August 15, 2020|archive-date=September 28, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928003820/https://www.espn.com/soccer/liverpool-engliverpool/story/4159360/liverpools-alexander-arnold-beats-rashford-pulisic-to-win-premier-league-young-player-of-the-season|url-status=live}}</ref>

Pulisic ended the season with 11 goals and 10 assists in all competitions.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Breakthrough Season: Christian Pulisic's Instant Impact |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/videos/v/2020/09/04/breakthrough-season--christian-pulisic-s-instant-impact-1FryC5aL|access-date=September 5, 2020 |website=chelseafc.com |language=en-UK|archive-date=October 24, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201024170520/https://www.chelseafc.com/en/videos/v/2020/09/04/breakthrough-season--christian-pulisic-s-instant-impact-1FryC5aL|url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2020–21: Champions League victory ====
[[File:Christian Pulisic FC Zenit vs Chelsea 8 December 2021.jpg|thumb|Pulisic (right) with Chelsea in December 2021]]
Ahead of his second season at Chelsea, Pulisic was given the number 10 shirt after [[Willian (footballer, born 1988)|Willian]], who wore the number the previous season, departed in the offseason to Arsenal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2020/09/09/chelsea-2020-21-squad-numbers-confirmed |title=Chelsea 2020/21 squad numbers confirmed |website=chelseafc.com |date=September 9, 2020|access-date=September 10, 2020|archive-date=September 29, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200929042408/https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2020/09/09/chelsea-2020-21-squad-numbers-confirmed|url-status=live}}</ref> He returned to training on September 9 following the hamstring injury he suffered in the FA Cup Final in August,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/chelsea/news/frank-lampard-christian-pulisic-in-contention-for-chelsea-vs-brighton |title=Christian Pulisic 'in contention' for Chelsea's Premier League opener against Brighton |first=Matt |last=Debono |website=Sports Illustrated |date=September 10, 2020|access-date=September 10, 2020|archive-date=April 15, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415031036/https://www.si.com/soccer/chelsea/news/frank-lampard-christian-pulisic-in-contention-for-chelsea-vs-brighton|url-status=live}}</ref> although Lampard kept him off the squad for the season opener against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton]] after experiencing some discomfort later in the week.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/chelsea/news/frank-lampard-has-revealed-why-christian-pulisic-missed-chelseas-3-1-win-against-brighton-in-the-premier-league |title=Frank Lampard reveals why Christian Pulisic missed 3–1 win against Brighton |date=September 14, 2020 |website=Sports Illustrated|access-date=September 15, 2020|archive-date=September 30, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200930002722/https://www.si.com/soccer/chelsea/news/frank-lampard-has-revealed-why-christian-pulisic-missed-chelseas-3-1-win-against-brighton-in-the-premier-league|url-status=live}}</ref>

Pulisic made his season debut on October 3, coming off the bench late in a 4–0 win over Crystal Palace.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/premier-league-chelsea-4-0-crystal-palace-christian-pulisic-season-debut-142638053.html |title=Premier League: Chelsea stomps Crystal Palace 4–0 as Christian Pulisic makes season debut |first=Doug |last=McIntyre |work=Yahoo Sports |date=October 3, 2020|access-date=October 28, 2020|archive-date=October 30, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030223654/https://sports.yahoo.com/premier-league-chelsea-4-0-crystal-palace-christian-pulisic-season-debut-142638053.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his first Premier League start of the season on October 17, a 3–3 draw against [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/premier-league-christian-pulisics-magic-cant-save-leaky-chelsea-against-southampton-video-162634963.html |title=Christian Pulisic makes first start of season but can't save leaky Chelsea against Southampton |first=Doug |last=McIntyre |work=Yahoo Sports |date=October 17, 2020|access-date=October 28, 2020|archive-date=October 31, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201031093341/https://sports.yahoo.com/premier-league-christian-pulisics-magic-cant-save-leaky-chelsea-against-southampton-video-162634963.html|url-status=live}}</ref> On October 28, Pulisic came off the bench to score a 90th-minute goal in a 4–0 Champions League away win against [[FC Krasnodar|Krasnodar]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Tom |last=Rostance |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54713315 |title=FK Krasnodar 0–4 Chelsea: Hakim Ziyech and Christian Pulisic strikes put seal on emphatic Champions League win in Russia |date=October 28, 2020 |website=[[BBC Sport]]|access-date=October 28, 2020|archive-date=October 28, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028202205/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54713315|url-status=live}}</ref> With his 93rd-minute goal for Chelsea against [[Chelsea F.C.–Leeds United F.C. rivalry|rivals]] [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] on December 5, Pulisic became the fastest American to reach 10 goals in the Premier League.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2020/12/record-christian-pulisic-becomes-fastest-american-to-10-epl-goals |title=PREMIER LEAGUE RECORD: Christian Pulisic is Fastest American to 10 EPL Goals |date=December 5, 2020 |website=ussoccer.com|access-date=December 6, 2020|archive-date=December 5, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205220812/https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2020/12/record-christian-pulisic-becomes-fastest-american-to-10-epl-goals|url-status=live}}</ref>

On April 3, 2021, Pulisic scored the opening goal in a 2–5 home league defeat to [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Chowdhury |first=Saj |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56546577 |title=Chelsea 2–5 West Brom: Baggies thump five past 10-man Blues |publisher=BBC Sport |date=April 3, 2021|access-date=April 3, 2021|archive-date=May 6, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210506140247/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56546577|url-status=live}}</ref> A week later, Pulisic scored a double against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] in a 4–1 victory at [[Selhurst Park]].<ref>{{cite news |date=April 10, 2021 |title=Pulisic brace vs. Crystal Palace keeps Chelsea on track for Champions League spot |work=[[ESPN]] |url=https://tv5.espn.com/football/report?gameId=578353|access-date=April 10, 2021|archive-date=April 10, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210410185318/https://tv5.espn.com/football/report?gameId=578353|url-status=live}}</ref> On April 24, he tied [[Lionel Messi]] for the record of most fouls won in a [[UEFA Champions League]] match with 11 against [[FC Porto|Porto]].<ref name=":7">{{Cite web |last=Ellis |first=Michael |date=April 14, 2021 |title=Christian Pulisic draws record number of fouls against in 10 years in Porto game |url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/chelsea-2021-04-14-christian-pulisic-draw-record-number-of-fouls-against-in-10-years-in-porto-game/ |access-date=July 6, 2023 |website=Tribuna.com |language=en}}</ref> On April 27, Pulisic scored Chelsea's only goal in a 1–1 away draw against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] at the [[Alfredo Di Stéfano Stadium|Estadio Alfredo Di Stéfano]] in the first leg of the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Real Madrid v Chelsea|Champions League semi-final]] tie, becoming the youngest Chelsea player and first American to score in the Champions League semi-finals.<ref name=":1">{{cite news |last=McNulty |first=Phil |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56880436 |title=Champions League semi-final: Karim Benzema earns Real Madrid draw against Chelsea |publisher=BBC Sport |date=April 27, 2021|access-date=April 27, 2021|archive-date=December 1, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221201073501/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56880436|url-status=live}}</ref> In the return game at Stamford Bridge, Pulisic came on as a substitute and provided the assist for [[Mason Mount]]'s late goal to make it 2–0 and secure passage to the [[2021 UEFA Champions League Final|final]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Murray |first=Scott |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2021/may/05/chelsea-v-real-madrid-champions-league-semi-final-second-leg-live |title=Chelsea 2–0 Real Madrid (3–1 agg): Champions League semi-final – as it happened |publisher=guardian.com |date=May 6, 2021|access-date=May 6, 2021|archive-date=May 5, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210505231232/https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2021/may/05/chelsea-v-real-madrid-champions-league-semi-final-second-leg-live|url-status=live}}</ref> On May 29, Pulisic won his first Champions League after Chelsea won 1–0 against Manchester City in the [[2021 UEFA Champions League Final|final]] at the [[Estádio do Dragão]] in Porto, becoming the first American to play in a UEFA Champions League Final<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0269-12650cedca55-37515f69768e-1000--report-chelsea-claim-second-title/ |title=Man. City 0–1 Chelsea: Havertz gives Blues second Champions League triumph |website=[[UEFA]] |date=May 29, 2021|access-date=May 29, 2021|archive-date=June 3, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603073706/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0269-12650cedca55-37515f69768e-1000--report-chelsea-claim-second-title/|url-status=live}}</ref> and the second American to win it after [[Jovan Kirovski]] in [[1996–97 UEFA Champions League|1997]] with Borussia Dortmund.<ref name=":3">{{cite news |title=Pulisic becomes first American to play in and win men's Champions League final |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4211221/2021/05/29/pulisic-becomes-first-american-to-play-in-and-win-mens-champions-league-final/ |work=[[The Athletic]] |date=May 30, 2021 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20210601200147/https://theathletic.com/news/christian-pulisic-champions-league-final-chelsea-man-city/HZ7lqB3lzuVa |archive-date=June 1, 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Christian Pulisic's Champions League win with Chelsea headlines an American run on European silverware |url=https://www.espn.in/football/english-premier-league/story/4396429/premier-league-grades-chelsealeedsman-city-top-of-the-class-as-arsenal-flounder |date=May 31, 2021 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20210601194824/https://www.espn.in/football/english-premier-league/story/4396429/premier-league-grades-chelsealeedsman-city-top-of-the-class-as-arsenal-flounder |archive-date=June 1, 2021 |last=Karlsen |first=Tor-Kristian |work=ESPN}}</ref>

==== 2021–23: Super Cup, Club World Cup, and departure ====
[[File:2021 FIFA Club World Cup Final - 10.jpg|thumb|Pulisic (middle) during the [[2021 FIFA Club World Cup final]]]]
On August 11, 2021, Pulisic won the [[2021 UEFA Super Cup]] and scored in the [[penalty shootout]]. Three days later, he scored in Chelsea's opening game of the [[2021–22 Premier League]] season, a 3–0 win over [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Chelsea 3–0 Crystal Palace |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58124898 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=August 14, 2021|access-date=April 19, 2022|archive-date=April 19, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220419213455/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58124898|url-status=live}}</ref> He tested positive for [[COVID-19]] the next week, and did not play again until November because of an ankle injury.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Christian Pulisic injury update: Tuchel confirms latest ankle setback |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/christian-pulisic-injury-update-chelsea-tuchel-ankle/1ao1ys2t591qe1hyu3zyxnarln |website=The Sporting News |date=October 20, 2021 |access-date=April 19, 2022|archive-date=April 19, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220419213455/https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/christian-pulisic-injury-update-chelsea-tuchel-ankle/1ao1ys2t591qe1hyu3zyxnarln|url-status=live}}</ref> On January 2, 2022, he scored the equalizer in a 2–2 draw at home against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Chelsea 2–2 Liverpool |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59792567 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=January 2, 2022|access-date=April 19, 2022|archive-date=April 11, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220411225633/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59792567|url-status=live}}</ref> He then came on early as a substitute in the [[2021 FIFA Club World Cup Final]], helping Chelsea to a 2–1 over [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]].<ref name=":8">{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0271-143308c604e5-48d7851a3e61-1000--chelsea-set-for-club-world-cup/ |title=Club World Cup: Champions League holders Chelsea become eight European winner |website=UEFA |date=February 12, 2022|access-date=April 19, 2022|archive-date=May 31, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220531100431/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0271-143308c604e5-48d7851a3e61-1000--chelsea-set-for-club-world-cup/|url-status=live}}</ref> He started the [[2022 EFL Cup Final|EFL Cup Final]] against Liverpool on February 27 as Chelsea lost on [[Penalty shootout|penalties]] after a 0–0 draw.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Chelsea 0–0 Liverpool AET (10–11 on pens): Reds win Carabao Cup after Kepa Arrizabalaga misses crucial penalty |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11938/12553258/chelsea-0-0-liverpool-aet-10-11-on-pens-reds-win-carabao-cup-after-kepa-arrizabalaga-misses-crucial-penalty |website=Sky Sports|access-date=April 19, 2022|archive-date=April 24, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220424182233/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11938/12553258/chelsea-0-0-liverpool-aet-10-11-on-pens-reds-win-carabao-cup-after-kepa-arrizabalaga-misses-crucial-penalty|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored in both legs of the club's [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] last 16 tie against [[Lille OSC|Lille]], as Chelsea progressed to the quarter-finals, 4–1 on aggregate.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Lille 1–2 Chelsea (agg 1–4 Lille) |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/60755067 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=March 16, 2022|access-date=April 19, 2022|archive-date=April 19, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220419220502/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/60755067|url-status=live}}</ref>

On October 8, 2022, Pulisic scored in his first start under new Chelsea manager [[Graham Potter]], a 3–0 win over [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 8, 2022 |title=Pulisic 8/10 helps Chelsea to smooth win over Wolves |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/chelsea-engchelsea/story/4763972/christian-pulisic-goal-helps-chelsea-to-win-over-wolves |access-date=October 9, 2022 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |archive-date=October 8, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221008162055/https://www.espn.com/soccer/chelsea-engchelsea/story/4763972/christian-pulisic-goal-helps-chelsea-to-win-over-wolves |url-status=live}}</ref> After an increasing lack of starts during the [[2022–23 Chelsea F.C. season|2022–23 season]] following Chelsea's rapid purchasing of new attackers and a shuffle of managers, it was speculated that he was going to leave the club before his contract ended in 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-03-07 |title=Report: Christian Pulisic set to leave Chelsea this summer; Manchester United interested |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/soccer/news/christian-pulisic-set-to-leave-chelsea-this-summer-report |access-date=2024-06-05 |website=NBC Sports |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-05-02 |title=What happened to Christian Pulisic at Chelsea? Explaining why USMNT star is not a starter for Blues {{!}} Sporting News |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/what-happened-christian-pulisic-chelsea-usmnt-start/qenltvch7novyppb9tckza3x |access-date=2024-06-05 |website=www.sportingnews.com |language=en-us}}</ref> Several clubs were interested, most notably [[AC Milan]], [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]], [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]], and [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-07-05 |title=Christian Pulisic new club after Chelsea: Potential transfer destinations for USMNT star as AC Milan bid {{!}} Sporting News |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/christian-pulisic-new-club-chelsea-transfer-usmnt-top-5/yobptlrkcpvykpyvqeerigwc |access-date=2024-06-05 |website=www.sportingnews.com |language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-06-04 |title=How Pulisic could fit at Juve, other potential destinations |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37760667/how-pulisic-fit-juventus-other-potential-destinations |access-date=2024-06-05 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref>

=== AC Milan ===
On July 13, 2023, Pulisic completed a transfer to [[Serie A]] club [[AC Milan]] on a four-year contract until June 30, 2027, and was given the number 11 previously worn by [[Zlatan Ibrahimović]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Christian Pulisic, new signing of the AC Milan transfer market: the official statement |url=http://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2023-07-13/official-statement-christian-pulisic |access-date=July 13, 2023 |website=AC Milan |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Christian Pulisic joins AC Milan |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/christian-pulisic-joins-ac-milan |access-date=July 13, 2023 |website=Chelsea FC |language=en-gb}}</ref> The transfer was executed through a deal worth a maximum of €22 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=July 13, 2023 |title=USMNT star Pulisic completes AC milan move |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37943676/usa-christian-pulisic-ac-milan-transfer-chelsea |access-date=July 13, 2023 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Twomey |first=James Horncastle and Liam |title=USMNT's Pulisic completes transfer to AC Milan from Chelsea |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4685441/2023/07/13/christian-pulisic-transfer-milan-chelsea-usmnt/ |access-date=July 13, 2023 |website=The Athletic |language=en}}</ref>

==== 2023–24: Return to form in Italy ====
On August 21, Pulisic made his Serie A debut for Milan, scoring the club's second goal 2–0 win against [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]], which in turn, made him the first American to score a goal in three of Europe's [[Big Five (association football)|Top five leagues]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |title=Christian Pulisic Scores Debut Goal for AC Milan vs Bologna (Video) – Sports Illustrated |language=en-us |magazine=Sports Illustrated |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2023/08/21/christian-pulisic-scores-goal-debut-ac-milan-bologna-video |access-date=August 21, 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=OptaJack |title=3 – Christian Pulisic is the first American to score a goal in three of the five major European leagues (Bundesliga, Premier League, Serie A). Journey. |url=https://twitter.com/OptaJack/status/1693709509099725270 |access-date=August 21, 2023 |website=Twitter |language=en}}</ref> In the following game on August 26, he opened Milan's 4–1 home win against [[Torino FC|Torino]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=August 26, 2023 |title=AC Milan 4-1 Torino: Christian Pulisic's fine form continues with goal in win for Rossoneri |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/serie-a/2022-2023/ac-milan-v-torino-serie-a-live_sto9759760/story.shtml |access-date=August 26, 2023 |website=Eurosport |language=en}}</ref> leading him to be named the club's Player of the Month for August.<ref>{{Cite web |title=USMNT star Christian Pulisic named AC Milan's Player of the Month for August |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/usmnt-star-christian-pulisic-named-ac-milans-player-of-the-month-for-august |access-date=September 6, 2023 |website=FOX Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> On October 7, Pulisic scored a last-minute winner in a dramatic 1–0 win over [[Genoa CFC|Genoa]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 7, 2023 |title=Made in the USA! USMNT stars Christian Pulisic and Yunus Musah combine as AC Milan top Genoa in chaotic clash that sees both goalkeepes sent off {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/yunus-musah-christian-pulisic-ac-milan-usmnt-genoa/blt3f3481bbf7b981cb |access-date=October 7, 2023 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> On December 2, he scored his fifth league goal from a long-ball kick from goalkeeper [[Mike Maignan]] in the 3–1 win over [[Frosinone Calcio|Frosinone]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=December 2, 2023 |title=USMNT star Christian Pulisic steals the show but Yunush Musah remains quiet as AC Milan bounce back from Dortmund disappointment with comfortable win over Frosinone {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/usmnt-christian-pulisic-yunush-musah-ac-milan-dortmund-win-frosinone/blt7580539e2a4b2b41 |access-date=December 2, 2023 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> On December 13, he scored his first [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] goal with Milan in the essential 2–1 win over [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] in the final game of the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League group stage#Newcastle United v Milan|group stage]], which kept his team in European competition with the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=December 13, 2023 |title=Watch: Pulisic equalises for Milan against Newcastle |url=https://sempremilan.com/watch-pulisic-equalises-milan-newcastle |access-date=December 13, 2023 |website=SempreMilancom |language=en}}</ref> On December 30, he scored in the 1–0 win against [[US Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] at [[San Siro]], which he broke the record for the most Serie A goals (6) by an American player in a single season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=AC Milan 1-0 Sassuolo (Dec 30, 2023) Game Analysis |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/679393 |access-date=2023-12-30 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Bandini |first=Nicky |date=2023-12-21 |title=Christian Pulisic has been a bright spot in a frustrating Milan season |language=en-GB |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/dec/21/christian-pulisic-milan-usmnt-stefano-pioli-serie-a |access-date=2023-12-31 |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> He was named [[Serie A Player of the Month]] for December with 2 goals and 2 assists in league play, becoming the award's first-ever North American recipient.<ref name=":9" />

On February 18, 2024, he came off the bench against [[AC Monza|Monza]] and recorded a goal and an assist to level the score 2–2, though Milan would lose 2–4.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-02-18 |title=What a waste! Milan squander Christian Pulisic's superstar performance as USMNT scores and assists in loss to Monza {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/waste-milan-squander-christian-pulisic-superstar-performance-usmnt-forward-scores-assists-dramatic-loss-monza/blt9016bc7b4fe17a5b |access-date=2024-02-21 |website=www.goal.com |language=en}}</ref> On March 2 in a dramatic 1–0 victory against [[SS Lazio|Lazio]], he caused two opposing players to receive [[Red card (association football)|red card]] dismissals. Following the match, he subsequently received death threats by Lazio fans, though his performance was praised by [[Stefano Pioli]] and his teammates.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-02 |title=Pulisic sent death threats after Milan-Lazio game |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/39640810/christian-pulisic-sent-death-threats-milan-lazio-game |access-date=2024-03-03 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=says |first=Albert |date=2024-03-01 |title=Pioli storms out of press conference defending Pulisic |url=https://football-italia.net/pioli-storms-out-of-press-conference-defending-pulisic/ |access-date=2024-03-03 |website=football-italia.net |language=en-GB}}</ref> On March 7 and 14, Pulisic scored in both legs against [[Slavia Prague]] in the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League#Round of 16|Round of 16]], tallying his first ever Europa League goals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-14 |title=Christian Pulisic is ready for USMNT duty! American star scores 11th of campaign as Milan dominate Slavia Prague to advance in Europa League {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/christian-pulisic-usmnt-scores-11th-goal-milan-dominate-slavia-prague-advance-europa-league/blt357415482b7c9ba7 |access-date=2024-03-19 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> Three days later, on March 17, he scored the second goal in a 3–1 away victory over [[Hellas Verona FC|Hellas Verona]]. It was the first time in his senior career that he had reached the tally of 12 goals within a single season.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.milannews.it/news/pulisic-da-record-non-aveva-mai-segnato-cosi-tanti-gol-a-questo-punto-della-stagione-529003 | title=Pulisic da record: Non aveva mai segnato così tanti gol a questo punto della stagione }}</ref> Moreover, the goal turned out to have some historical significance, becoming AC Milan's 5000th in the Serie A since the start of competition.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.milannews.it/news/pulisic-segna-la-rete-numero-5000-del-milan-in-serie-a-l-ultimo-in-cifra-tonda-fu-kaka-528805 | title=Pulisic segna la rete numero 5000 del Milan in Serie A. l'Ultimo in cifra tonda fu Kakà }}</ref> On April 6, he scored his 10th Serie A goal against [[US Lecce|Lecce]], which broke his career highest league seasonal goal tally.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-04-06 |title=Pulisic achieves personal-best league goal tally |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/39888267/usa-christian-pulisic-personal-best-league-goal-season-milan |access-date=2024-04-07 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> On May 11, Pulisic scored two league goals in the 5–1 victory over [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]], recording his first brace with Milan.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-05-11 |title=Christian Pulisic is sensational! USMNT star scores brilliant brace as AC Milan thump Cagliari in Serie A {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/christian-pulisic-sensational-usmnt-scores-ac-milan-cagliari-serie-a/blt9701f99ee9c8fc90 |access-date=2024-05-11 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref>

Following his debut Serie A season, he was considered the best Italian signing of [[2023–24 Serie A|2023–24]] with his personal record of 15 goals and 10 assists across all competitions.<ref name=":12">{{Cite web |date=2024-05-30 |title=Serie A superlatives: Christian Pulisic and Lautaro Martinez shine; Jose Mourinho fails at Roma |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/serie-a-superlatives-christian-pulisic-and-lautaro-martinez-shine-jose-mourinho-fails-at-roma/ |access-date=2024-06-05 |website=CBS Sports |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-06-05 |title=How Pulisic and Milan's 2023/24 signings have been a roaring success |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/how-pulisic-and-milans-202324-signings-have-been-a-roaring-success-39244723 |access-date=2024-06-05 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> Pulisic was listed on the 3-man final shortlist of the [[Serie A Awards|Serie A Midfielder of the Season]] award with [[Hakan Çalhanoğlu]] and [[Teun Koopmeiners]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-05-21 |title=USMNT star Christian Pulisic named finalist for Serie A Midfielder of the Season award {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/usmnt-christian-pulisic-serie-a-midfielder-of-season-award/bltfd2022261b48cbe5 |access-date=2024-05-23 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> He was named on the [[2023–24 Serie A#Seasonal awards|2023–24 Serie A Team of the Season]].<ref name=":11">{{cite news |date=24 May 2024 |title=EA Sports FC 24 – Serie A Team of the Season |url=https://www.legaseriea.it/en/media/serie-a/ea-sports-tm-fc-24-serie-a-team-of-the-season-3 |access-date=24 May 2024 |publisher=Serie A}}</ref>

==== 2024–25: Supercoppa Italiana and AC Milan top scorer ====
[[File:Milan Cagliari 2025 - Pulisic.jpg|thumb|Pulisic playing for Milan during the [[2024–25 Serie A|2024-25 Serie A]] season]]
On August 24, 2024, he scored his first goal of the [[2024–25 Serie A]] in the 1–2 defeat to [[Parma Calcio 1913|Parma]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-24 |title=WATCH: Christian Pulisic scores as AC Milan lose 2-1 to newly promoted Parma in Serie A |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/watch-christian-pulisic-scores-as-ac-milan-lose-2-1-to-newly-promoted-parma-in-serie-a/ |access-date=2024-08-24 |website=CBS Sports |language=en}}</ref> On September 14 he recorded an assist and penalty goal in the 4–0 win over [[Venezia FC|Venezia]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-14 |title=Christian Pulisic Bags Goal and Assist for AC Milan in Nine Minutes |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/christian-pulisic-bags-assist-and-goal-for-ac-milan-in-nine-minutes |access-date=2024-09-15 |website=SI |language=en-US}}</ref> In Milan's opening [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] game on September 17, he scored the first goal in the 1–3 defeat to [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-17 |title=Christian Pulisic, with a Champions League-opening goal, is establishing himself as a star |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/christian-pulisic-with-a-champions-league-opening-goal-is-establishing-himself-as-a-star-210132295.html?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAFdBJXyUi4dLEvF4reVMBkFE4rUhDL-XOSot0HUHewm5CWIN7GJb03spmOkqhAiXK0jcoIA3tFsbSm-VKeW6Wg_b3R_AQv-HQ8HWy-ftnt62vagv5QZLorNBoePp5UBsY35sqT2dhvSvTLy9TmWxDuVMfmx14T6AGvsGrsk7gN6P |access-date=2024-09-17 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> In the following game on September 22, he scored the opener in the 2–1 [[Derby della Madonnina]] win over rivals [[Inter Milan|Inter]] by dribbling past 4 defenders in a solo effort.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Milan 2-1 Inter Milan (Sep 22, 2024) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/712157 |access-date=2024-09-22 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> On September 27, he scored in his fourth-straight club game, a 3–0 win over [[US Lecce|Lecce]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-27 |title=WATCH: USMNT's Christian Pulisic scores fourth Serie A goal of season vs. Lecce for AC Milan {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/usmnt-christian-pulisic-scores-serie-a-goal-lecce-ac-milan/bltc2c2ccde8d35952a |access-date=2024-09-28 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> On October 6, in the 1–2 loss against [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] he scored a volley goal. During the match, Fiorentina conceded two penalties during the game, both of which saw Pulisic controversially stripped of his penalty-taker status by teammates [[Théo Hernandez]] and [[Tammy Abraham]], both of whom missed their penalties. After the match, [[Paulo Fonseca]] was angered by Hernandez and Abraham's actions and cemented Pulisic as the Milan penalty taker: "Of course I am upset. Christian should take penalties. It must never happen again, and I told the players."<ref>{{Cite web |last=says |first=Rosario |date=2024-10-06 |title=Fonseca insists Pulisic must take Milan penalties: 'Never again' |url=https://football-italia.net/fonseca-insists-pulisic-take-milan-penalties/ |access-date=2024-10-06 |website=football-italia.net |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-10-06 |title=Fonseca explains why he subbed off star duo and labels penalty calls a 'circus' |url=https://sempremilan.com/fonseca-explains-subbed-star-duo-penalty-circus |access-date=2024-10-06 |website=SempreMilancom |language=en}}</ref> Pulisic became the first player from a top-five European league to contribute to a goal in seven consecutive league matches.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-10-20 |title=Another first for on-fire USMNT ace Christian Pulisic! AC Milan's American forward beats Premier League, Serie A, La Liga, Ligue 1 & Bundesliga stars to notable achievement {{!}} Goal.com UK |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/another-first-usmnt-ace-christian-pulisic-ac-milan-american-forward-beats-premier-league-serie-a-la-liga-ligue-1-bundesliga-stars-achievement/blt6aaac40b69269cfe#csc07c713a8a3826a4 |access-date=2024-10-21 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-GB}}</ref> On October 22, he scored an [[Olympico goal|Olimpico goal]] in the 3–1 Champions League win over [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-10-22 |title=Pulisic scores 'Olimpico' goal for Milan in UCL |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/41944740/christian-pulisic-olimpico-goal-corner-ac-milan-ucl-brugge |access-date=2024-10-22 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> On November 5, he assisted [[Malick Thiaw]] in the 3–1 Champions League win over [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Chief |title=CHRISTIAN PULISIC AND AC MILAN TAKE DOWN REAL MADRID |url=https://www.barstoolsports.com/blog/3530339/christian-pulisic-and-ac-milan-take-down-real-madrid |access-date=2024-11-05 |website=www.barstoolsports.com |language=en}}</ref>

On January 6, 2025, Pulisic won the [[2024–25 Supercoppa Italiana]] against rivals [[Inter Milan]], where he scored the equalizer and created a critical game-winning pass to [[Rafael Leão]] in an eventual 3–2 comeback victory, securing his first trophy with AC Milan. He finished as the tournament's joint-top goalscorer.<ref>{{Cite news |last=O'Keeffe |first=Greg |title=Christian Pulisic inspires Milan to Super Cup win, clinches his first trophy for the club |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6042672/2025/01/06/pulisic-ac-milan-super-cup-win/ |access-date=2025-01-06 |work=[[The Athletic]] |date=January 6, 2025  |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Schneider |title=USMNT's Christian Pulisic and teammate Rafael Leao inspire incredible AC Milan comeback in Supercoppa Italiana final vs. Inter to claim first trophy of season |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/usmnt-christian-pulisic-rafael-leao-ac-milan-supercoppa-italiana-final-vs-inter-yunus-musah/blt25a0125e86a64791 |access-date=2025-01-06 |work=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> Pulisic's goal made him the first American player in a top five European league since [[Clint Dempsey]] to reach double figures in consecutive seasons.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Inter 2-3 AC Milan: Abraham last-gasp strike snatches Supercoppa Italiana glory |url=https://www.fotmob.com/news/39rr37qo3v5r14c6imridlfjq-inter-2-3-ac-milan-abraham-last-gasp-strike-snatches-supercoppa-italiana-glory |access-date=2025-01-06 |work=FotMob |language=en}}</ref> After a perfect record of 12 in a row, Pulisic failed to convert a penalty kick for the first time in his professional career when his shot was blocked by [[Torino FC|Torino]]'s goalkeeper [[Vanja Milinković-Savić]], ending in a 1–2 defeat on February 22.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-02-22 |title=Christian Pulisic fails to convert a penalty kick for the 1st time in his professional career |url=https://apnews.com/article/christian-pulisic-penalty-miss-1a6aad4fc02563c4880071bb667b6a70 |access-date=2025-03-09 |website=AP News |language=en}}</ref> On March 8 he scored a brace in the late 3–2 comeback victory over [[US Lecce|Lecce]], including winning and converting the game-winning penalty.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-03-08 |title=Pulisic scores 2 to give Milan 'very important' win |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/44166997/christian-pulisic-ac-milan-2-goals-leece-serie-important-win |access-date=2025-03-09 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> On April 27 he scored against [[Venezia FC|Venezia]], breaking his highest scoring season with 16 goals across all competitions.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-04-27 |title=WATCH: USMNT star Christian Pulisic scores his 16th goal of season for AC Milan in win vs. Venezia |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/watch-usmnt-star-christian-pulisic-scores-his-16th-goal-of-season-for-ac-milan-in-win-vs-venezia/ |access-date=2025-04-27 |website=CBS Sports |language=en}}</ref>

He finished the season as AC Milan's top scorer with 17 goals along with 10 assists across all competitions.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-05-24 |title=USMNT's Christian Pulisic and AC Milan end 2024-25 Serie A campaign with scrappy win over already-relegated Monza {{!}} Goal.com English Oman |url=https://www.goal.com/en-om/lists/usmnt-s-christian-pulisic-and-ac-milan-end-2024-25-serie-a-campaign-with-scrappy-win-over-already-relegated-monza/blt1b5b9b235c024b5a#cs6f52c7b7001b4879 |access-date=2025-05-25 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-OM}}</ref> He had 9 league assists, the second highest in the Serie A behind [[Romelu Lukaku]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Serie A Top Scorers |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/italian-serie-a/top-scorers#TopAssists |access-date=2025-05-25 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

Pulisic was listed on the [[2024–25 Serie A#Seasonal awards|2024–25 Serie A Team of the Season]], his second consecutive appearance.<ref name=":17">{{Cite web |last=Arts |first=Electronic |date=2025-05-16 |title=Serie A Enilive Team of the Season (TOTS) - EA SPORTS FC™ Ultimate Team - EA SPORTS Official Site |url=https://www.ea.com/games/ea-sports-fc/fc-25/tots/serie-a |access-date=2025-05-16 |website=Electronic Arts Inc. |language=en}}</ref>

==== 2025–26 ====
On August 17, 2025, Pulisic scored in Milan's opening [[2025–26 Coppa Italia]] game, a 2–0 win against [[SSC Bari|Bari]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-08-17 |title=Pulisic scores, Modric debuts in Milan Coppa win |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/46003221/pulisic-scores-milan-safely-advance-bari-coppa-italia |access-date=2025-08-18 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> On September 21, he scored a brace and created an assist in the 3–0 win against [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]], which Pulisic surpassed the record of [[Clint Dempsey]] (57) of having the most goals in the top-5 European leagues as an American with 59.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-21 |title=Gallery: 'Super Pulisic', 'Scudetto-worthy Milan' - Today's front pages in Italy |url=https://sempremilan.com/gallery-super-pulisic-milan-papers-italy |access-date=2025-09-21 |website=SempreMilan |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Milan 3-0 Udinese (Sep 20, 2025) Game Analysis |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/736818 |access-date=2025-09-21 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> On September 28, Pulisic created an assist in a solo run from his own half and later scored a goal in the 2–1 victory over Serie A leaders [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]], claiming Milan's place at the top of the league.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-28 |title=Serie A {{!}} AC Milan 2-1 Napoli: Pulisic inspirational as leaders crumble |url=https://football-italia.net/serie-a-milan-2-1-napoli-pulisic-inspirational/ |access-date=2025-09-28 |language=en-GB}}</ref> In [[2025–26 Serie A#Monthly awards|September]], he won his second [[Serie A Player of the Month]] award with three goals and two assists in 147 minutes of league play.<ref name=":19">{{cite press release |title="Christian Pulisic "EA SPORTS FC Player Of The Month" for September" |url=https://en.legaseriea.it/serie-a/news/christian-pulisic-ea-sports-fc-potm-for-september |date=9 October 2025 |access-date=9 October 2025 |publisher=Serie A}}</ref> Returning from a month long injury, he scored the winner in the 1–0 [[Derby della Madonnina]] over [[Inter Milan|Inter]], which made him tied as the Serie A goalscoring leader.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Bosher |first=Luke |date=2025-11-23 |title=USMNT's Christian Pulisic scores winner in Milan derby, goes top of Serie A scoring charts |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6831695/2025/11/23/christian-pulisic-milan-inter-usmnt/ |access-date=2025-11-23 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> On December 8 where Milan was down 1–2 against [[Torino FC|Torino]], Pulisic came off the bench with an [[influenza]] fever to score a brace ultimately making a 3–2 comeback win to keep Milan as the league leaders, which commentators drew comparisons to [[Michael Jordan]]'s 1997 [[flu game]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-12-08 |title=Serie A {{!}} Torino 2-3 AC Milan: Pulisic fever completes comeback victory |url=https://football-italia.net/serie-a-torino-2-3-ac-milan-pulisic-fever-win/ |access-date=2025-12-08 |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-12-09 |title='I was truly dead' - Christian Pulisic reveals battle against flu after 'really ill' USMNT star fires AC Milan past Torino with dazzling two-goal display {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/christian-pulisic-flu-ill-usmnt-star-ac-milan-torino-two-goal/blt061ce20281eda9c5 |access-date=2025-12-09 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Vertelney |first=Seth |title=Pulisic dubs Torino masterclass his 'flu game' |url=https://prosoccerwire.usatoday.com/story/sports/usmnt/2025/12/09/ac-milan-star-pulisic-calls-torino-match-his-flu-game/87683862007/ |access-date=2026-03-31 |website=Pro Soccer Wire |language=en-US}}</ref> After his 10th goal, Pulisic suffered a series of further injuries starting in late December, causing limited or inconsistent play compared to his record-breaking first half of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-03-27 |title=Why is Christian Pulisic struggling? Injuries, a new role and questions about Milan future slowed USMNT's star |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/christian-pulisic-struggling-injuries-milan-usmnt/ |access-date=2026-03-31 |website=CBS Sports |language=en}}</ref> Around the same time, Milan manager [[Massimiliano Allegri]] shifted him and teammate [[Rafael Leão]] primarily into centralized [[Striker (soccer)|striker]] positions away their typical winger positions, where Pulisic failed to score another goal by the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Fisher |first=Oliver |date=2026-05-31 |title=GdS: Role, jeers, droughts and arguments - what made Leao decide to leave Milan |url=https://sempremilan.com/what-made-leao-decide-leave-milan |access-date=2026-06-01 |website=SempreMilan |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-06-01 |title=Christian Pulisic ending five-month goal drought in huge USMNT weight lifted |url=https://nypost.com/2026/06/01/sports/christian-pulisic-wastes-no-time-ending-five-month-goal-drought-in-huge-usmnt-weight-lifted/ |access-date=2026-06-01 |language=en-US}}</ref>

== International career ==

=== 2012–2015: Youth level ===
Pulisic represented the United States at [[United States boys' national under-15 soccer team|U-15]] and [[United States men's national under-17 soccer team|U-17]] levels. He scored two goals in 10 appearances for the under-15 team.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ussoccer.com/teams/youth/us-under15-boys/schedule-results/2013.aspx |title=2013 schedule & results |publisher=U.S. Soccer |access-date=August 17, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106084002/http://www.ussoccer.com/teams/youth/us-under15-boys/schedule-results/2013.aspx |archive-date=January 6, 2014 |url-status=dead}}</ref> On December 13, 2013, for the U-17 team, he played [[Brazil national under-17 football team|Brazil]] at a U17 friendly tournament in Florida where he scored a goal in the championship 4–1 win.<ref name=":5" /> He captained the U-17 team at the [[2015 FIFA U-17 World Cup]], where he scored a goal and an assist in three games.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/u17worldcup/matches/round=271783/match=300298362/match-report.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151021134443/http://www.fifa.com/u17worldcup/matches/round=271783/match=300298362/match-report.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=October 21, 2015 |title=FIFA U-17 World Cup Chile 2015 – Matches – USA 2:2 (2:0) Croatia – FIFA.com |work=FIFA.com}}</ref> During his two years with the team, Pulisic scored a total of 20 goals in 34 games.<ref>{{cite news |title=American Exports: Jurgen Klinsmann lauds Christian Pulisic's "tremendous" talent after U17 star's Bundesliga debut |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/american-exports-jurgen-klinsmann-lauds-christian-pulisics-tremendous-talent-aft |website=mlssoccer.com |date=January 30, 2016 |access-date=August 17, 2022 |archive-date=August 17, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220817165632/https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/american-exports-jurgen-klinsmann-lauds-christian-pulisics-tremendous-talent-aft |url-status=live}}</ref> Pulisic had been eligible to play internationally for [[Croatian national football team|Croatia]] but declined the opportunity.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Straus |first1=Brian |title=Pulisic cap-tied to U.S. after playing in WCQ |url=https://www.si.com/planet-futbol/2016/03/29/christian-pulisic-usa-cap-tied-croatia-world-cup-qualifier |access-date=October 6, 2017 |magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]] |date=March 29, 2016 |language=en |archive-date=October 7, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171007115846/https://www.si.com/planet-futbol/2016/03/29/christian-pulisic-usa-cap-tied-croatia-world-cup-qualifier |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="odbio" />

=== 2016–2020: Senior debut and breaking USMNT records ===
[[File:USMNT vs. Trinidad and Tobago (48125059622) (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|upright|Pulisic with the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] in 2019.]]

On March 27, 2016, Pulisic was called up to the senior team by head coach [[Jürgen Klinsmann]] ahead of a World Cup [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – CONCACAF fourth round#Group C|qualifying game]] against [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Zusi, Pulisic Added to MNT Roster Ahead of Qualifying Match vs. Guatemala, Presented by Liberty Mutual Insurance, in Columbus |url=http://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2016/03/27/15/57/160327-mnt-klinsmann-adds-zusi-and-pulisic-to-world-cup-qualifying-roster |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190424084959/https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2016/03/27/15/57/160327-mnt-klinsmann-adds-zusi-and-pulisic-to-world-cup-qualifying-roster |archive-date=April 24, 2019 |access-date=March 27, 2016}}</ref> Two days later, he made his debut in that match, a 4–0 win at the [[Mapfre Stadium]] in [[Columbus, Ohio]], as an 81st-minute substitute for [[Graham Zusi]]. He thus became the youngest American to play in a World Cup qualifier.<ref name="history">{{cite news |date=March 30, 2016 |title=Pulisic makes history as USA beat Guatemala |url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Tournaments/noblmd28-pulisic-youngest-ever-usmnt-player-to-play-world-cup-qualifier-aged-17.jsp |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180726205616/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Tournaments/noblmd28-pulisic-youngest-ever-usmnt-player-to-play-world-cup-qualifier-aged-17.jsp |archive-date=July 26, 2018 |access-date=April 18, 2016 |publisher=Bundesliga}}</ref>

Pulisic was included in the senior squad for the [[Copa América Centenario]], which was hosted by the United States.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Floyd |first1=Thomas |date=May 21, 2016 |title=Pulisic included as USA unveils Copa America squad |url=http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/66/united-states/2016/05/21/23770382/pulisic-included-as-usa-unveils-copa-america-squad |access-date=May 28, 2016 |archive-date=October 20, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020044713/https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/66/united-states/2016/05/21/23770382/pulisic-included-as-usa-unveils-copa-america-squad |url-status=live}}</ref> A week later, he became the youngest player to score for the United States in the modern era, when he put home a late goal in a 4–0 [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] win against visiting side [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Chicharito and Pulisic chasing records at the Copa America – bundesliga.com |url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/noblmd33-javier-chicharito-hernandez-and-christian-pulisic-chasing-records-at-the-copa-america-centenario.jsp |access-date=August 31, 2016 |archive-date=August 19, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819003651/http://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/noblmd33-javier-chicharito-hernandez-and-christian-pulisic-chasing-records-at-the-copa-america-centenario.jsp |url-status=live}}</ref>

On September 2, 2016, Pulisic recorded two goals and an assist in a World Cup qualifying match in a 6–0 victory over [[Saint Vincent and the Grenadines national football team|Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2016/09/02/us-player-ratings-christian-pulisic-steals-show-qualifying-rout |title=US Player Ratings: Christian Pulisic steals the show in qualifying rout |work=MLSSoccer.com |access-date=September 3, 2016 |archive-date=October 26, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026224933/https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2016/09/02/us-player-ratings-christian-pulisic-steals-show-qualifying-rout |url-status=live}}</ref> thereby becoming the youngest person to score in a World Cup qualifier for the United States and the youngest player to score a brace in American history.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2016/09/02/22/51/160902-mnt-players-enter-record-book-as-team-steps-closer-to-hex-in-6-0-wcq-win-at-st-vincent |title=USA Players Enter Record Book as Team Steps Closer to Hex in 6–0 Qualifying Win at St. Vincent |website=www.ussoccer.com |access-date=September 3, 2016 |archive-date=July 23, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180723065547/https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2016/09/02/22/51/160902-mnt-players-enter-record-book-as-team-steps-closer-to-hex-in-6-0-wcq-win-at-st-vincent |url-status=live}}</ref> In the following match against [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]], he broke another youth record by becoming the youngest American to start a World Cup qualifying match.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/united-states/story/2945175/christian-pulisic-sets-record-as-youngest-american-to-start-world-cup-qualifier |title=Christian Pulisic becomes youngest U.S. player to start World Cup qualifier |work=ESPNFC.com |date=September 6, 2016 |access-date=September 7, 2016 |archive-date=August 2, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190802122038/http://www.espnfc.com/united-states/story/2945175/christian-pulisic-sets-record-as-youngest-american-to-start-world-cup-qualifier |url-status=live}}</ref> In the following year of qualification, on June 8, Pulisic scored both goals in a 2–0 victory over Trinidad and Tobago. In the last two matches of qualification, Pulisic scored a goal in each: a 4–0 victory over [[Panama national football team|Panama]] and a 1–2 defeat to Trinidad and Tobago. He finished the fifth round as the top scorer with five goals. Despite his strong performances, the United States failed to qualify for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]. The loss to Trinidad and Tobago is considered the most humiliating performance in American soccer history.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/team/united-states/660/blog/post/3227792/trinidad-and-tobago-loss-the-most-humiliating-in-united-states-soccer-history?src=com |title=Trinidad and Tobago loss the most humiliating in United States soccer history |work=espn.com |date=October 13, 2017 |access-date=October 25, 2019 |archive-date=October 25, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191025155748/https://www.espn.com/soccer/team/united-states/660/blog/post/3227792/trinidad-and-tobago-loss-the-most-humiliating-in-united-states-soccer-history%3Fsrc%3Dcom |url-status=live}}</ref>

On November 20, 2018, Pulisic became the youngest player to captain the United States national team in a friendly defeat to [[Italy national football team|Italy]]. Pulisic was 20 years and 63 days old.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/why-christian-pulisic-is-the-right-man-to-captain-the-usa-usmnt-dortmund-517955.jsp |title=10 reasons why Christian Pulisic is the right man to captain the USA |publisher=bundesliga.com |access-date=December 2, 2018 |archive-date=December 3, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181203055723/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/why-christian-pulisic-is-the-right-man-to-captain-the-usa-usmnt-dortmund-517955.jsp |url-status=live}}</ref>

On March 26, 2019, Christian Pulisic became the youngest United States player to score 10 international goals<ref>{{Cite web |title=Christian Pulisic Becomes Fastest MNT Player to Score 10 Goals |url=https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2019/03/christian-pulisic-becomes-fastest-mnt-player-to-score-10-goals|access-date=January 23, 2022 |website=www.ussoccer.com |language=en|archive-date=January 23, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220123202725/https://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2019/03/christian-pulisic-becomes-fastest-mnt-player-to-score-10-goals|url-status=live}}</ref> at 20 years, 189 days old.

=== 2021–present: CONCACAF triumphs and World Cup debut ===
On June 6, 2021, Pulisic captained the United States national team to a 3–2 victory in the first-ever [[2019–20 CONCACAF Nations League|CONCACAF Nations League]] [[2021 CONCACAF Nations League Final|final]] against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]], scoring the winning goal by converting a penalty in the 114th minute.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/jun/07/usa-mexico-concacaf-nations-league-soccer-final |title=Pulisic's extra-time winner seals Nations League title for USA over Mexico |website=The Guardian |date=June 7, 2021 |access-date=June 8, 2018 |archive-date=June 7, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210607050842/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/jun/07/usa-mexico-concacaf-nations-league-soccer-final |url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:2022 FIFA World Cup United States 1–1 Wales - (15).jpg|thumb|left|200px|Pulisic at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] against [[Wales national football team|Wales]].]]

On March 27, 2022, Pulisic scored his first international [[Hat-trick#Association football|hat-trick]] for the U.S. men's national team during their win over Panama in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – CONCACAF third round|2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]]. His first two goals from the hat trick came from penalty kicks.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2022/03/28/christian-pulisic-first-hat-trick-usmnt-vs-panama |title=Christian Pulisic Gets His First Hat Trick With USMNT Against Panama |website=Sports Illustrated |date=March 27, 2022 |access-date=March 30, 2022 |archive-date=March 28, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220328202618/https://www.si.com/soccer/2022/03/28/christian-pulisic-first-hat-trick-usmnt-vs-panama |url-status=live}}</ref>

At the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], Pulisic assisted [[Timothy Weah|Tim Weah]] for the team's opening group stage goal against [[Wales national football team|Wales]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Tim Weah scores USMNT's first World Cup goal since 2014 thanks to brilliant Christian Pulisic assist |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/tim-weah-scores-usmnts-first-world-cup-goal-since-2014-thanks-to-brilliant-christian-pulisic-assist/ |access-date=February 3, 2023 |website=CBS Sports |date=November 21, 2022 |language=en |archive-date=February 3, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230203043115/https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/tim-weah-scores-usmnts-first-world-cup-goal-since-2014-thanks-to-brilliant-christian-pulisic-assist/ |url-status=live}}</ref> He received his first FIFA World Cup Man of the Match award for his offensive pressure during the 0–0 draw against [[England national football team|England]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=World Cup: Pulisic named Player of the Match as England and USA can't be separated |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/world-cup-england-and-usa-cant-be-separated-in-second-group-game |access-date=February 3, 2023 |website=www.chelseafc.com |language=en-gb |archive-date=February 3, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230203043119/https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/world-cup-england-and-usa-cant-be-separated-in-second-group-game |url-status=live}}</ref> In the following game Pulisic earned his second Man of the Match award after scoring the winner in the United States' 1–0 win over [[Iran national football team|Iran]] in their last group stage game, sending his team to the knockouts.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63711992 |title=World Cup 2022: Iran 0–1 USA: Christian Pulisic winner seals date with Netherlands – BBC Sport |website=bbc.com |date=November 29, 2022 |access-date=November 29, 2022 |archive-date=November 29, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221129025317/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63711992 |url-status=live}}</ref> In the Round of 16, he assisted [[Haji Wright]]'s goal against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] as the United States was defeated 3–1. Pulisic, along with three other players, received the third most Man of the Match awards in the tournament with two, after [[Kylian Mbappé]]'s three and [[Lionel Messi]]'s four.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Nagpal |first=Saurabh |date=December 6, 2022 |title=The Most Man Of The Match Awards Won This World Cup 2022 |url=https://www.foottheball.com/fifa-world-cup/most-man-of-the-match-awards-won-2022/ |access-date=April 17, 2023 |website=FootTheBall |language=en-US |archive-date=April 17, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230417044247/https://www.foottheball.com/fifa-world-cup/most-man-of-the-match-awards-won-2022/ |url-status=live}}</ref>
[[File:Christian Pulisic USMNT v Portugal Mar 31 2026-99.jpg|thumb|upright|Pulisic in 2026]]
During the [[2023 CONCACAF Nations League Finals]], Pulisic scored a brace against Mexico in the semi-finals and was awarded Man of the Match.<ref>{{Cite web |date=June 16, 2023 |title=USMNT vs Mexico, summary: Game suspended, red card, score, goals & highlights {{!}} Concacaf Nations League |url=https://en.as.com/soccer/usmnt-vs-mexico-live-online-score-stats-updates-concacaf-nations-league-n/ |access-date=June 16, 2023 |website=Diario AS |language=en-us |archive-date=June 16, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230616060602/https://en.as.com/soccer/usmnt-vs-mexico-live-online-score-stats-updates-concacaf-nations-league-n/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The United States defeated Canada 2–0 in the final, leading to him achieving his second Nations League trophy in a row. He was awarded Player of the Tournament for the [[2022–23 CONCACAF Nations League|2022–23]] competition. In the following year's [[2024 CONCACAF Nations League Finals]], Pulisic captained the U.S. in the 2–0 victory against Mexico in [[2024 CONCACAF Nations League final|the final]] to secure his third Nations League trophy in a row.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Goff |first=Steven |date=2024-03-25 |title=With two stunning goals, USMNT beats Mexico, keeps Nations League title |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/2024/03/24/usmnt-nations-league-champions-mexico/ |access-date=2024-03-25 |newspaper=Washington Post |language=en-US |issn=0190-8286}}</ref>

Competing in the [[2024 Copa América]], he recorded a goal and assist in the opening 2–0 group stage win over [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] in [[2024 Copa América Group C|Group C]] and was awarded Man of the Match.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Pulisic scores, assists on Balogun goal to lead U.S. over Bolivia 2-0 in Copa America opener |url=https://www.foxsports.com/articles/soccer/pulisic-scores-assists-on-balogun-goal-to-lead-us-over-bolivia-20-in-copa-america-opener |access-date=2024-06-24 |website=FOX Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> On November 18, he became the fastest USMNT player to record 50 goal contributions after a goal against [[Jamaica national football team|Jamaica]] in the [[2024–25 CONCACAF Nations League|CONCACAF Nations League]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Johnson |first=Parker |date=2024-11-18 |title=Christian Pulisic Made USMNT History Against Jamaica |url=https://athlonsports.com/soccer/christian-pulisic-goal-vs-jamaica-made-usmnt-history |access-date=2024-11-19 |website=Athlon Sports |language=en}}</ref>

== Player profile ==

=== Style of play ===
Following his promotion to the Dortmund first team, ''[[FourFourTwo]]'' writer Andy Mitten wrote that the Dortmund manager [[Thomas Tuchel]] "saw the potential – the speed, sharpness, strength, sublime fitness and mature decision-making that belied his age".<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=Andy Mitten October 30, 2019 |title=Captain America: Can Christian Pulisic really fill the hole left by Eden Hazard for Chelsea? |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/chelsea-christian-pulisic-frank-lampard-andy-mitten-interview-profile-eden-hazard-usa|access-date=August 10, 2020 |website=fourfourtwo.com |date=October 30, 2019 |language=en|archive-date=July 27, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200727131351/https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/chelsea-christian-pulisic-frank-lampard-andy-mitten-interview-profile-eden-hazard-usa|url-status=live}}</ref> Tuchel called Pulisic "the kind of guy who's very self-confident, shows his talent on the pitch, and doesn't show any nerves under pressure – which is a wonderful combination".<ref name=":0" /> Pulisic's Dortmund teammate [[Nuri Şahin]] said, "He's fearless [...] He has so much speed, but what I like most is his first touch. When he gets the ball, his first touch opens up a huge space for him even if there's no space."<ref name=":0" /> Since the 2018–19 season, Pulisic was most often deployed on the wing for Dortmund, and this continued at Chelsea and AC Milan. At Milan, with the presence of [[Rafael Leão]] on the left of the attacking third, Pulisic once again moved to the right wing. However, in absence of Leão, Pulisic sometimes was deployed as a left winger, his traditionally preferred position.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/where-christian-pulisic-play-position-ac-milan-usmnt-transfer/blt0bac68854f40b73e|title=How Christian Pulisic will fit into AC Milan's line up - and what it means for the USMNT star's career &#124; Goal.com|date=July 14, 2023|website=www.goal.com}}</ref> He is also deployed regularly in central areas as a [[central attacking midfielder]] ("''trequartista")'' as Milan's attacking third's playmaker.<ref>{{cite web |title=U.S.'s Christian Pulisic 'not going to change' style in face of multiple fouls |url=http://www.espnfc.com/united-states/story/3221168/uss-christian-pulisic-not-going-to-change-style-in-face-of-multiple-fouls |first=Jeff |last=Carlisle |date=October 5, 2017 |access-date=October 12, 2017 |publisher=[[ESPN FC]] |archive-date=October 12, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171012201613/http://www.espnfc.com/united-states/story/3221168/uss-christian-pulisic-not-going-to-change-style-in-face-of-multiple-fouls |url-status=live}}</ref> Because of his direct style of play, Pulisic is often subjected to fouls by opponents, which he holds the [[UEFA Champions League]] record of the most fouled player in a single match with 11.<ref name=":28" />

In July 2020, Chelsea manager [[Frank Lampard]] compared him positively to former Chelsea winger [[Eden Hazard]], saying Pulisic "has a more direct attacking instinct. He has the talent to pass through defenders and run inside the box which is a great trait in the modern game." Lampard added, "There's still more development to come. Christian is taking responsibility to change games."<ref name=":2">{{Cite news |title=Lampard on Pulisic, Hazard comparisons |date=July 6, 2020 |url=https://www.soccer.nbcsports.com/2020/07/06/lampard-on-pulisic-hazard-comparisons/amp/|access-date=September 11, 2020 |website=nbcsports.com |first=Joe |last=Prince-Wright}}{{dead link|date=June 2023 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Pulisic has been praised by Milan manager [[Stefano Pioli]], as “He has quality, intensity and willingness." – “He’s scoring a lot, too, which isn’t always easy for a winger.”<ref>{{Cite web |last=O'Keeffe |first=Greg |title=Christian Pulisic has found a home away from home in Milan, and USMNT will benefit |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5356141/2024/03/21/pulisic-usmnt-milan-revival/ |access-date=2024-04-17 |website=The Athletic |date=March 22, 2024 |language=en}}</ref> Pulisic is routinely deployed as a [[central attacking midfielder]] ("''trequartista")'' as the attacking third's playmaker.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-04-05 |title=A new position for Christian Pulisic? AC Milan boss Stefano Pioli explains why USMNT star could in for a surprising change {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/christian-pulisic-new-position-ac-milan-squad-depth-stefano-pioli-reveals/blt90e8f2b02d224a55 |access-date=2024-04-17 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=":16" />

=== Reception ===
[[File:USA vs Por SS-9.jpg|thumb|alt=Christian Pulisic|Pulisic during pre-match ceremonies against Portugal on March 31, 2026]]
Pulisic is widely regarded as the most successful American club player of all time.<ref name=":22">{{Cite web |last=Reags |title=Christian Pulisic Is The Greatest American Soccer Player We've Ever Seen |url=https://www.barstoolsports.com/blog/3517782/christian-pulisic-is-the-greatest-american-soccer-player-weve-ever-seen |access-date=2024-09-26 |website=www.barstoolsports.com |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":20">{{Cite web |date=2025-01-10 |title=Ranking The 25 Best American Soccer Players Of All Time |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/ranking-the-25-best-american-soccer-players-of-all-time |access-date=2026-05-29 |website=SI |language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=":21">{{Cite web |date=2024-06-24 |title=Christian Pulisic isn't just USMNT's most accomplished player — he's the best there's ever been for USA {{!}} Sporting News |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/christian-pulisic-usmnt-best-player-ever-usa/2903fc5998590c7f573e2511 |access-date=2024-09-26 |website=www.sportingnews.com |language=en-us}}</ref> Pulisic is the all-time American top goalscorer and assist provider in the [[UEFA Champions League]], [[Serie A]], and the [[Big Five (association football)|top five European leagues]].<ref name=":23">{{Cite web |title=Most Goals By An American In Europe |url=https://www.statmuse.com/fc/ask/most-goals-by-an-american-in-europe |access-date=2026-05-29 |website=StatMuse |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":24" /> He was the first American to play in and win the UEFA Champions League, [[UEFA Super Cup]], and [[FIFA Club World Cup]]. Pulisic was the first American to score in an [[FA Cup final]], and the first North American to feature on a [[Serie A Player of the Month]] award, winning twice.

In his early club seasons with Borussia Dortmund he was regarded as one of the world's best young players; being listed 3rd on the 2017 [[Goal (website)#NXGN|NXGN]] list of the world's 50 best wonderkids under age 19,<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-20 |title=NXGN: Kylian Mbappe, Christian Pulisic and where 2017's best wonderkids are now {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/nxgn-2017-best-wonderkids/1s31weojaayp31xxxt1jmf27l7 |access-date=2024-09-26 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref> as a finalist (6th) of the 2017 [[Golden Boy (award)|Golden Boy]] award; presented to the best player in Europe under age 21,<ref name=":26" /> and as runner-up of the [[2018 Ballon d'Or#Kopa Trophy|2018]] [[Kopa Trophy]] to [[Kylian Mbappé]]; presented to the world's best player under age 21.<ref name=":13">{{Cite web |date=2018-12-03 |title=Pulisic finishes second to Mbappe in Young Player Award voting - SBI Soccer |url=https://sbisoccer.com/2018/12/pulisic-finishes-second-to-mbappe-in-young-player-award-voting |access-date=2024-09-26 |website=sbisoccer.com |language=en-US}}</ref> During his time with Chelsea he was initially praised for his talent and attacking directness, becoming the youngest Chelsea player to score a [[hat-trick]],<ref name=":27" /> but was increasingly criticized for being heavily injury-prone; having missed 53 club games from a series of injuries spanning his 4 seasons.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Off to AC Milan - Why Christian Pulisic never quite worked out at Chelsea |url=https://www.transfermarkt.us/off-to-ac-milan-why-christian-pulisic-never-quite-worked-out-at-chelsea/view/news/424162 |access-date=2024-09-26 |website=www.transfermarkt.us |language=en}}</ref> Following his move to AC Milan, Pulisic rebounded his injury record and club form, being praised as one of the best players in the Italian Serie A, as well as one of the club's most important players.<ref name=":11" /><ref name=":12" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Ruthven |first=Graham |date=2024-09-26 |title=Fast and furious: this is the best version of Christian Pulisic we've ever seen |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/sep/26/fast-and-furious-this-is-the-best-version-of-christian-pulisic-weve-ever-seen#:~:text=Milan%20supporters%20are%20used%20to,assists%20in%20just%20five%20games. |access-date=2024-09-26 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-12-18 |title=How Christian Pulisic quietly became Serie A's best player: Versatility, formation change and consistency key |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/christian-pulisic-best-serie-a-player-how-it-happened/ |access-date=2026-05-29 |website=CBS Sports |language=en}}</ref>

Pulisic since a young age has been frequently debated as the greatest American player of all time with [[United States men's national soccer team|U.S. national team]] legends [[Landon Donovan]] and [[Clint Dempsey]], as well as one of the best North American players of all time.<ref name=":22" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-01 |title=Is Christian Pulisic the USMNT's best player ever? If not, who takes that distinction? |url=https://www.marca.com/en/world-cup/2022/12/01/6388ee4c22601d784a8b45ab.html |access-date=2024-09-26 |website=MARCA |language=en}}</ref><ref name=":20" /><ref name=":21" /> At only age 25 he tied Donovan's career record of four [[U.S. Soccer Player of the Year]] awards. He is regarded as one of the two best active [[CONCACAF]] players worldwide with [[Alphonso Davies]].<ref name=":14">{{cite news |date=June 6, 2024 |title=Golazo 100 countdown: Ranking the best men's soccer players in the world for 2024 |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/golazo-100-countdown-ranking-the-best-mens-soccer-players-in-the-world-for-2024/ |access-date=June 7, 2024 |website=CBS Sports}}</ref><ref name=":15">{{cite web |date=June 4, 2024 |title=2024 FC 100: Haaland among best forwards in men's soccer |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/40006322/erling-haaland-best-forwards-men-soccer |access-date=June 24, 2024 |website=ESPN}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-24 |title=CONCACAF Player Power Rankings: USMNT's Christian Pulisic and Canada's Alphonso Davies rule in the region {{!}} Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/concacaf-player-power-rankings-usmnt-mexico-canada-christian-pulisic-alphonso-davies/blt9cbda3c570f5935c |access-date=2024-09-26 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-11-11 |title=The 25 best right wingers in world football - ranked |url=https://www.90min.com/posts/the-25-best-right-wingers-in-world-football-ranked |access-date=2025-01-26 |website=90min.com |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Ritchie |first=Calum |date=2024-03-05 |title=Ranking the 15 best wingers in world football right now - in order |url=https://www.givemesport.com/best-wingers-in-world-football-ranked/ |access-date=2025-01-26 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref> Pulisic has been known to exceptionally perform for the U.S. national team despite historic club form struggles, most notably at Chelsea.<ref>{{Cite web |title='He'll Score At The World Cup': Christian Pulisic's Goal Drought Doesn't Worry USA Coach |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/hell-score-world-cup-christian-pulisics-goal-drought-doesnt-worry-usa-coach |access-date=2026-05-29 |website=www.foxsports.com |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Maurer |first=Pablo Iglesias |last2=Rueter |first2=Jeff |date=2026-05-28 |title=Pochettino says Christian Pulisic ‘is going to score in the World Cup’ |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/may/28/mauricio-pochettino-christian-pulisic-usmnt |access-date=2026-05-29 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Pulisic's status of captaining the United States national team with his high level of play has earned him the nickname "[[Captain America]]" by fans and other players.<ref name=":4">{{cite web |last1=Kwesi |first1=Marcus |date=August 2020 |title=Christian Pulisic Is 'Captain America' After Scoring Goal In FA Cup Final |url=https://nesn.com/2020/08/christian-pulisic-is-captain-america-after-scoring-goal-in-fa-cup-final/#:~:text=and%20Privacy%20Policy-,Christian%20Pulisic%20Is%20'Captain%20America'%20After%20Scoring,Goal%20In%20FA%20Cup%20Final&text=After%20Pulisic%20scored%2C%20his%20nickname,has%20been%20played%20since%201872. |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220531175624/https://nesn.com/2020/08/christian-pulisic-is-captain-america-after-scoring-goal-in-fa-cup-final/#:~:text=and%20Privacy%20Policy-,Christian%20Pulisic%20Is%20'Captain%20America'%20After%20Scoring,Goal%20In%20FA%20Cup%20Final&text=After%20Pulisic%20scored%2C%20his%20nickname,has%20been%20played%20since%201872. |archive-date=May 31, 2022 |access-date=April 28, 2021}}</ref> He has also been nicknamed "The [[LeBron James]] of Soccer" due to a clip from the television show ''[[Pawn Stars]]'', which has since become a meme.<ref>{{Cite web |date=January 2, 2022 |title=Christian Pulisic the LeBron James of soccer? Explaining the 'Pawn Stars' reference that lit up Twitter |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/christian-pulisic-lebron-james-soccer-pawn-stars-twitter/owf11qpeqpv3zsmqy7qwo9j1 |last=Borg |first=Simon |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220902003715/https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/christian-pulisic-lebron-james-soccer-pawn-stars-twitter/owf11qpeqpv3zsmqy7qwo9j1 |archive-date=September 2, 2022 |access-date=September 2, 2022 |website=www.sportingnews.com |language=en}}</ref>

Pulisic's paternal grandfather, Mate Pulišić, was born on the Croatian island of [[Olib]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.croatia.org/crown/articles/10920/1/Christian-Pulisic-rising-USA-soccer-star-in-Germany-has-Croatian-roots.html |title=Christian Pulisic rising USA soccer star in Germany has Croatian roots |website=www.croatia.org |access-date=February 23, 2019 |archive-date=January 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190103004841/http://www.croatia.org/crown/articles/10920/1/Christian-Pulisic-rising-USA-soccer-star-in-Germany-has-Croatian-roots.html |url-status=live}}</ref> In a 2023 interview for ESPN, Pulisic added that his paternal grandmother Johanna DiStefano was [[Sicilian Americans|Sicilian]], noting that "My dad, her son, has an Italian flag tattooed on his forearm".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/38006000/after-chelsea-pulisic-embraces-ac-milan-italian-roots |title=After Chelsea, Pulisic embraces AC Milan and Italian roots |first=Graham |last=Hunter |website=ESPN.com |date=July 13, 2023 |access-date=July 13, 2023}}</ref> Pulisic obtained [[Croatian nationality law|Croatian citizenship]] after moving to Germany in order to avoid applying for a German [[Work permit|work visa]], which is required to work in the country without a [[European Union]] passport.<ref name="odbio">{{cite news |title=Pulisic nikada neće postati Pulišić |url=http://slobodnadalmacija.hr/sport/domaci-nogomet/clanak/id/307420/pulisic-nikada-nece-postati-pulisic |access-date=November 11, 2016 |publisher=Slobodna Dalmacija |language=hr |date=March 31, 2016 |archive-date=November 11, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111200752/http://slobodnadalmacija.hr/sport/domaci-nogomet/clanak/id/307420/pulisic-nikada-nece-postati-pulisic |url-status=live}}</ref> Pulisic has a cousin, [[Will Pulisic]], who previously played for [[MLS Next Pro]] team [[Minnesota United FC 2]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=MNUFC2 |title=Roster {{!}} Will Pulisic |url=https://www.mnufc.com/mnufc2/roster/players/will-pulisic |access-date=September 27, 2023 |website=MNUFC2 |language=en |archive-date=September 27, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230927192855/https://www.mnufc.com/mnufc2/roster/players/will-pulisic |url-status=dead }}</ref>

Pulisic is a practicing [[Catholic Church in the United States|Catholic]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sportsspectrum.com/sport/soccer/2021/01/21/usmnt-christian-pulisic-closer-to-god |title=USMNT star Christian Pulisic says he's grown closer to God in past year |date=January 21, 2021 | access-date=October 3, 2022 | archive-date=October 5, 2022 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221005221321/https://sportsspectrum.com/sport/soccer/2021/01/21/usmnt-christian-pulisic-closer-to-god/ | url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Restaurant Tour of Hershey: Christian Pulisic Jersey: Raffle |url=http://www.sjafestival.com/restaurant-tour-of-hershey-christian-pulisic-jersey-raffle.html |access-date=November 6, 2022 |website=St. Joan of Arc Festival |language=en |archive-date=November 6, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221106031618/http://www.sjafestival.com/restaurant-tour-of-hershey-christian-pulisic-jersey-raffle.html |url-status=live}}</ref> He occasionally posts Bible verses on his social media accounts.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/CfhOUxNJ9_C/?igshid=YmMyMTA2M2Y= |title=Christian on Instagram: "1 Peter 4:8–10" | access-date=October 3, 2022 | archive-date=October 3, 2022 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221003073037/https://www.instagram.com/p/CfhOUxNJ9_C/?igshid=YmMyMTA2M2Y= | url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Ciakx0EIhcE/?igshid=YmMyMTA2M2Y= |title=Christian on Instagram: "Psalm 147:11" | access-date=October 3, 2022 | archive-date=October 3, 2022 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221003073039/https://www.instagram.com/p/Ciakx0EIhcE/?igshid=YmMyMTA2M2Y= | url-status=live}}</ref>

Outside of soccer, Pulisic is a fan of the [[New York Jets]], [[New York Rangers]], and [[Philadelphia 76ers]].<ref>{{Citation |title=Christian Pulisic joins Kyle Martino at Chelsea training ground |date=August 9, 2019 |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/video/christian-pulisic-joins-kyle-martino-chelsea-training-ground |access-date=August 11, 2019 |archive-date=August 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811131934/https://www.nbcsports.com/video/christian-pulisic-joins-kyle-martino-chelsea-training-ground |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Citation |title=PRE-MATCH PRESS CONFERENCE |date=March 23, 2022 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T_j-W-fvbgw&t=618s |access-date=March 25, 2022 |archive-date=March 25, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220325185322/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T_j-W-fvbgw&t=618s |url-status=live}}</ref> Pulisic is a fan of the [[Ford Mustang]] and imported a left-hand drive [[Shelby Mustang#Ford Performance 3rd generation Shelby GT500 (2020–2022)|Shelby GT500]] to England from the United States in 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Morgan |first=Thomas |date=December 2, 2022 |title=Check Out Christian Pulisic's Stunning Ford Shelby GT500 |url=https://www.hotcars.com/christian-pulisic-ford-mustang-shelby-gt500/ |access-date=February 11, 2023 |website=HotCars |language=en |archive-date=February 11, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230211024450/https://www.hotcars.com/christian-pulisic-ford-mustang-shelby-gt500/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Citation |title=Christian Pulisic & Ben Chilwell of Chelsea FC on Fave World Cup Moments & Best Rappers {{!}} GOAT Talk | date=August 2, 2022 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sXhktM3b86M |language=en |access-date=February 11, 2023 |archive-date=February 11, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230211024448/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sXhktM3b86M |url-status=live }}</ref>

In 2021, Pulisic signed a long term sponsorship deal with German sportswear brand [[Puma (brand)|Puma]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://about.puma.com/en/newsroom/news/puma-announces-blockbuster-signing-christian-pulisic | title=Puma Announces Blockbuster Signing of Christian Pulisic &#124; Puma® }}</ref> On October 11, 2022, he released an autobiography titled ''Pulisic: My Journey So Far''. The book chronicles his journey into the soccer world.<ref name=":6">{{Cite web |title=Review of Christian Pulisic book, "My Journey So Far" |url=https://worldsoccertalk.com/news/review-of-christian-pulisic-book-my-journey-so-far-20221113-WST-407904.html |access-date=November 16, 2022 |website=World Soccer Talk |date=November 13, 2022 |language=en |archive-date=November 16, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221116080813/https://worldsoccertalk.com/news/review-of-christian-pulisic-book-my-journey-so-far-20221113-WST-407904.html |url-status=live}}</ref> In the book, he also revealed that he suffered with depression while he was injured in 2020 and during times that he did not get much playing time.<ref name=":5" /> In June 2024, [[CBS Sports]] announced the beginning of the filming process for the [[docuseries]] ''PULISIC'', which would include details about Pulisic's personal life, professional career and involvement in the [[2024 Copa América]], and was set to be released on [[Paramount+]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Booth |first=Chuck |date=1 June 2024 |title=Christian Pulisic documentary series will premiere this fall on Paramount+ chronicling the USMNT star's life |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/christian-pulisic-documentary-series-will-premiere-this-fall-on-paramount-chronicling-the-usmnt-stars-life/ |access-date=2 June 2024 |work=[[CBS Sports]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=West |first=Jenna |date=1 June 2024 |title=Pulisic documentary coming to Paramount+ this fall |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5533987/2024/06/01/christian-pulisic-documentary-usmnt/ |access-date=2 June 2024 |work=[[The Athletic]]  |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>
From June 2024 to April 2026 he was in a relationship with American golfer Alexa Melton.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://athlonsports.com/soccer/usmnt-christian-pulisic-admission-about-girlfriend-alexa-melton-is-turning-heads}}</ref>

